title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine in heavy pan.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack in Bundt pan.
Put in refrigerator for at least 3 days.
Remove from pan.
Keep refrigerated until all eaten.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Put ingredients in Ziploc bag and mix well.
Coat chicken well.
Place chicken in Pam coated pan.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and pepper in oil until tender but not brown.
Add tomato sauce, bay leaves, salt, sugar, chili powder, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for about 45 minutes. Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water and stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Add shrimp and simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or as soup with crackers.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together corn meal, flour, oil, egg, sugar, corn and cottage cheese.
Place half of mixture into pan.
Sprinkle with half of the Cheddar cheese.
Spread on the chilies.
Cover with the rest of mixture and sprinkle the rest of cheese on top.

title: spiced beets
directions: Mix and bring to boil and pour over can of red beets.
When beets have been used up cook a few carrots until about half done, slice lengthwise and drop in the spiced vinegar.
Let stand several hours.

title: chicken scampi 'n' linguine
directions: Put on kettle of water (for amount see linguine label) to boil for linguine.
Bone chicken breasts and cut meat into 1-inch pieces.
Heat butter or margarine and oil in a large skillet.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cook, stirring constantly until golden.
Push to one side.
Add broccoli and red pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and cook 2 minutes.

title: snack pizza
directions: Oil a baking sheet.
Put each biscuit into a 4-inch circle. Place on cookie sheet.
Mix the tomato sauce and oregano in a measuring cup.
Spoon some on each biscuit.
Spoon mushrooms over tomato sauce.
Put a few slices of meat on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake about 8 minutes or until crust is light brown.

title: crisp cucumber sticks
directions: Slice and soak cucumbers in lime water 24 hours.
Drain and soak 4 hours in fresh water changing every hour.
Use alum in first water.
Boil sugar, vinegar and spices.
Pour hot over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, boil 1 hour.
Seal in jars.

title: quick lemon chicken
directions: Pat chicken dry with a paper towel.
Heat butter and oil in skillet over medium high heat.
Coat chicken with flour and season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with a few drops of lemon juice. Cook chicken until brown on each side, about 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.
To the pan juices, add the remaining juice.
Simmer about 5 minutes, then pour over chicken.

title: holiday bread
directions: Melt the butter and add milk and 1/2 cup warm water and set aside.
Mix yeast with 1/2 cup of warm water (it should bubble, if not start over), add to the other liquid above.
Mix all ingredients and knead.
Make a ball and lightly cover with oil, then push down and cover a blanket.
Let stand 3 - 4 hours, knead again and again cover with a blanket for 1 more hour.
Make 5 loaves and place on 3 greased baking sheets, cover with a blanket for 1/2 hour more.
Beat 2 eggs in a bowl and brush on bread, make a cross in the dough with a sharp knife and bake at 325 degrees for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Melt butter and add flour, pecans and brown sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for a 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread onto crust. Mix puddings, vanilla and milk.
Spread on cake.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and drizzle with Hershey's chocolate or mint pieces.

title: halupki
directions: Choose cabbage (not too solid); pare around core and remove core.
In large pot, bring water to boil; preboil cabbage.
Leaves will fall off; remove leaves as they wilt.
Cool leaves; use paring knife to remove thick center ridge.
Mix next 5 ingredients together; place heaping tablespoon into center of leaf; roll up. Shred center small leaves of cabbage.
In bottom of pot, lay rolled cabbage on shredded cabbage.
Next, cover with mixture of tomato soup and tomatoes.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: spamwiches
directions: Mix well in a large bowl the Spam, soup, onion and cheese. Spread mixture on both the tops and bottoms of buns. Place (open-faced) on baking sheet and toast in broiler until cheese melts and slightly browns. Serve hot.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, salt and water in two large bowls. Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours. Add sugar and vinegar; stir until sugar dissolves. Pack into 1 pint freezer containers, leaving 1 inch head space. Cover and freeze for up to 6 weeks. Thaw at room temperature 4 hours before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and chilies.
Mix all together; heat and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients except cloves and water.
Steep cloves 15 minutes in boiling water; add to other mixture.
Serve hot. Yields 16 servings.

title: kerry's seafood gumbo
directions: Gumbo should be a two day project. Peel and cut your shrimp and chop your vegetables one day and refrigerate them. The next day, making gumbo along with a good bottle of wine will be a happy thing. Start with two stainless steel skillets. In one start the roux by combining 3/4 cup oil and 1/2 cup flour over a low fire, and stir constantly. It usually takes an hour and 15 min. to make the roux. You may also need to add a little more oil so that it is like a medium thick gravy. Stir it until it becomes brown and the flour sort of separates from the oil. At the same time, in the other skillet, put in the remainder of the oil and saute the okra and the white onions until they are wilted. Add the remaining vegetables with the salt and pepper and stir them until they are wilted and soft. When the roux is ready, add it to the vegetables and mix well. Transfer your gumbo to a soup pot. Start adding your boiling water, Rotel, chicken broth, shrimp and remaining ingredients. Cook on a low heat for about 4 hours. About 30 min. before serving add your crab meat. Serve over rice and let the GUMBO PARTY BEGIN!

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, the 1/4 cup melted oleo, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in thawed potatoes. Turn the potato and cheese mixture into prepared baking dish. Toss together the corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted oleo. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for about one hour or until casserole is golden and potatoes are tender.
tags: frozen loose pack hash brown potatoes

title: round steak with rich gravy(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Cut steaks into 5 or 6 serving size pieces.
Place in slow cooking (crock) pot.
Add dry onion soup mix, water and condensed mushroom soup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Excellent served with mashed potatoes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: sunday dinner chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat both cans of soup and milk together until well blended.
Pour over rice.
Place chicken over rice mixture and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Do not add salt.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 hours at 325°.

title: muriel's frosting
directions: Beat together and mix the first 3 ingredients, then, using only 3/4 of the Cool Whip, add and beat.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion; drain.
Add soups, vegetables, rice, water, celery, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in a few Tater Tots.
Put the rest on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a wire whisk.
Spread half down the centers of the loaves of thawed Rhodes bread.
Save the other half, then place a layer of Mozzarella cheese, layer of pepperoni and/or layer of mushrooms and/or layer of green peppers, then a layer of Provolone cheese.
Bring the front of the loaf back and back of the loaf forward.
Pinch together at top of loaf. Pinch ends together and fold under.
Pour remaining half of mixture on top of loaves.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir until well mixed by hand.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake jelly roll pan size 20 to 30 minutes, 9 x 13-inch pan size 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, salad oil and pumpkin well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add pie filling and stir in nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured bread pan.
Check at end of 1 hour; it may need to bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes
in half or wedges.
Arrange potatoes peel side down
in
shallow
baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush on potatoes.

title: sugar plums
directions: Melt butter in frying pan, adding sugar, eggs, salt and dates. Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla, walnuts, and Rice Krispies.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Makes 40 sugar plums.
These freeze well.

title: 8 or 12 layer chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and powder together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until done.
Thin layer in 8-inch cake pan.

title: chicken or beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a large ziploc bag with 2 1/2 pounds of meat. Whole tri-tip or whole skinless chicken breasts work best). Marinate for a minimum of 1-2 days.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar and cut in butter until crumbly. Spread in a 9 x 13 aluminum pan and pat down evenly.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Do not brown.
Beat well eggs, sugar, flour, baking powder and lemon juice.
Pour over baked crust. Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
May dust with powdered sugar

title: dirty pudding
directions: Mix milk, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add pudding mix. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups scalded milk over the first 4 ingredients. Reserve 1/2 cup milk.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast to lukewarm milk.
Add yeast and milk to first mixture.
Add the eggs and then flour.
Work in a cup at a time as you may not need all the flour.
Knead and put in a greased bowl.
Grease top and cover with warm moist towel.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: date pudding ii
directions: Pour hot
water over dates and soda.
Dissolve and let set until cool. Mix
the remainder of ingredients, then add date mixture.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan and bake.
When ready to serve, crumble cake in a dish alternately
with
vanilla pudding.
Serve with whipped cream.
You can also add miniature marshmallows and bananas.

title: cherry brunch muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease bottoms of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg, stir in milk, oil and cherry syrup.
Mix in flour, 1/4 cup sugar, cherries, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in order listed in bowl mixing well. Pour into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool bread in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Put wafers, pecans, raisins and cherries in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix with your hands.
This will be a stiff mixture.
Make into an 18 inch loaf.
Wrap in waxed paper, then in a thick towel.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours before cutting.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In blender, combine strawberry soda, lemon sherbet and whole strawberries. Blend until smooth. Pour into 2 glasses. Top with Reddi-Wip. Sprinkle with ground cinnamon.

title: homemade clay for youngsters
directions: Combine in a saucepan the cornstarch and baking soda.
Add cold water to which food coloring has been added.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook a minute longer or until mixture looks like moist mashed potatoes.
Remove from heat. Transfer to plate.
Cover with a damp towel and when cool enough to handle, knead a little as you would dough.
Pack in a plastic bag.
May add color to make colors.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, coconut and pecans together and freeze.
Once frozen, roll into small balls and stick toothpicks into each ball.
Melt chocolate chips and wax.
Dip balls into hot mixture.
Drop onto wax paper to cool.
Freeze until eaten.

title: 15 minute chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 5 minutes in saucepan.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind cookies in blender or food processor until it looks like potting soil (will do better if frozen).
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Prepare pudding with milk according to directions.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookies and creamed mixture in alternate layers in a 10-inch flower pot, lined with foil or individual paper cups. Finish with dirt (cookie) layer on top.
Decorate with artificial flowers or gummy worms.
Good for classroom parties.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Alternate the potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread mixture evenly over potatoes.
Decorate with ketchup, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: potato donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
It may require more flour, depending on the weather.
Also, you may use leftover mashed potatoes and a little less plain water.
After ingredients are mixed, roll or flatten to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out donuts.
Deep fry in grease. Be sure to remove excess flour from donuts to keep grease clear.

title: fat free cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place vanilla wafer in lined muffin tin.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sour cream, egg substitute, flour and extract.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon over wafers until tin is full.
Bake 18 minutes, then turn oven off and leave for 2 minutes.
Open oven door and leave for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: mexitalian lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, cook chili powder and ground beef; drain.
In large bowl, combine ground beef, drained salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, combine cottage cheese and parsley.

title: frosting paint
directions: Beat with mixer.
Paint or spread on baked cookies.
Thin with water, if needed.
After painting, let frosting dry before stacking cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, butter, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Arrange in alternate layers with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese is well melted.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add cooked rice and broccoli. Mix well.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the oleo and chocolate together.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add melted mixture to the other mixture.
Last, add vanilla and pecans.
Bake in brownie pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for a couple of hours. Serves 6.

title: pork roast with sauerkraut
directions: Roast pork until done.
Save drippings to make drippings gravy.
Lift roast out of roaster; place on platter.
Saute sauerkraut in frypan or skillet with a couple of tablespoons butter and 2 heaping tablespoons of brown sugar.
Cook on low heat until well blended or about 30 minutes.
Place this around roast after slicing.

title: spam stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain.
Rinse in cold water.

title: squash surprise
directions: Cook until tender the squash; drain and then add sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well and place in baking dish.
Stir-fry slices of 2 apples in margarine, sugar and water. When tender, add pineapple and raisins.
Spoon into squash and top with brown sugar, flour, melted margarine and pecans; bake until slightly brown and serve.

title: easy pudding pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine together.
Press in a 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° or until browned.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Cook in the microwave.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: To prepare either sauce, combine all of the listed ingredients in a small bowl; mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Each recipe makes about 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: easy buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water in large bowl.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
When shortening is melted, add cold water and egg.
Remove from heat.

title: twinkie cake dessert
directions: Place Twinkies in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Slice bananas on top. Cook undrained pineapple and sugar in pan 10 minutes.
Pour over Twinkies.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Pour over pineapple mixture. Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Chill.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: In oven, saute onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Add the next 9 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add shrimp and parsley.
Simmer, uncovered, until shrimp are cooked, approximately 7 to 10 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Slice oranges.
If needed, add sugar.
Combine oranges, coconut, cherries and pecans.
Serve with a dollop of cream.

title: crab and shrimp au gratin
directions: Drain cans of crab and shrimp; set aside in an extra large lasagna pan.
Saute onion and butter for 5 minutes.
Add cream and salt and pepper to taste.
Add sauteed mixture to crab, shrimp and krab mixture.
Add grated Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes; uncover and continue to bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: sugar-free jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn down TV.
Remove toys from counter. Measure 2 cups of flour.
Get baking powder.
Remove Dustin's hand from flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Vacuum mixture off kitchen floor (that Dustin spilled).
Get egg.
Answer telephone.
Separate egg and warm baby Alison's bottle.
Help Susie figure out new math problem (the old reliable way).
Grease pan; salesman at door.
Take 1/4-inch of salt from greased pan and look for Dustin.
Put mess in wastebasket; dishes in dishwasher.
Call bakery.
Take aspirin.

title: easy cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water and chill until partially thickened.
Peel orange and cut in very small pieces. Fold orange, pineapple, cranberry sauce and nuts into gelatin. Pour into a quart dish or mold until firm.

title: georgia powell's green bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole dish.
Put buttered Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Use 1/2 roll of crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Form into small balls. Roll in coconut.
Store in covered container in cool place.
Makes about 75.
Best after a day or so.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Mix well and pour over 8 chicken breast halves.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.
Easy and good.

title: uncle hootie's bubble bread
directions: Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Drizzle garlic butter over both halves.
Toast in oven for 1 or 2 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread 1/2 jar Blue cheese dressing over bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, paprika and parsley.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pickle relish
directions: Soak cut up cucumbers in lime and water for 24 hours.
Wash until water is clear.
Chop cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Add pimento.

title: bread and butter pickles(squash)
directions: Heat to boiling, but do not boil.
Put in cleaned hot jars.
If you like, use cucumbers instead of squash.
Very good.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash, onions and peppers (chopped small). Cover with ice.
Mix and let stand 1 hour (pick out ice or let mixture stand until ice has melted).
Drain.
Combine pimentos, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; bring to a boil. Add squash mixture to boiler and boil for 2 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: chocolate-peppermint dessert
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, margarine and egg yolks.
Add melted baking chocolate, salt, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Crush graham crackers or vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour in filling and freeze 2 hours or overnight.
Spread 1 quart peppermint ice cream over chocolate; put some of the crumbs on top and freeze.
It helps to put ice cream in refrigerator when you put chocolate layer in the freezer; this way the ice cream is softened enough to spread well in 2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rotel casserole
directions: Heat meat and onion together and brown.
Drain.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Put chips in bottom of pan.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Add 1/2 pound cheese over mixture.
Bake until cheese melts in oven at 350°.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until creamy, then cook until hard boil or hard ball stage.
Mix vanilla and nuts, beating again until creamy.
Work fast.
Break with fork.

title: indian fruit pudding
directions: Trim crust from bread; cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Line a 1 1/2-quart round bowl with bread, pressing firmly with fingers. Cook plums with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon, stirring constantly until plums are soft, about 10 minutes.
Cook peaches with 2/3 cup sugar, about 10 minutes.
Layer plums and peaches in bread-lined bowl.
Cover top with remaining bread slices.
Place a flat plate with a heavy weight on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Unmold and serve with whipped cream (Cool-Whip).

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, oleo, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in medium bowl with wooden spoon until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoon about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease baking dish; slice potato and place one half in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle with half of the onion and seasoning (this should be used sparingly).
Add the ham and cover with remaining half of potato and onions.
Add milk and if it is too much for the dish, hold and add gradually during cooking process.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° until potato is cooked through and brown on top, about 20 minutes.
Contains 299 calories per serving.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Place flour in pie plates and make hole in center.
Pour the other ingredients in and mix well.
Press into pie plate and bake according to pie directions.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mix potatoes, 1 stick butter, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.

title: standing rib beef roast
directions: About noon on the day you are going to serve it, take the meat out of the refrigerator and let it stand at room temperature for about an hour.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease a round pizza pan.
Roll dough into a circular shape onto pizza pan.
Bake until golden brown.
Next, mix cream cheese and Cool Whip until completely blended.
Let chill in refrigerator.
Cool cookie pizza.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place the apple slices in a buttered dish.
Cream the sugar, flour and butter; cover apples with this mixture and bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: gail's italian macaroni salad
directions: *I use low-fat kind.

title: romaine and cucumber salad with garlic vinaigrette
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together the vinegar, garlic paste and pepper to taste.
Add oil in a stream, whisking and whisk the vinaigrette until it is emulsified.
Add the romaine and the cucumbers and toss the salad well.

title: pears poached in wine sauce
directions: Peel pears. Combine wine, sugar, lemon and cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil.
Add pears.
Cover and poach until just tender. Remove pears.
Mix cornstarch with a small amount of water, then add to wine mixture.
Cook, stirring until clear and thickened. Arrange pears on serving dish and spoon over wine sauce.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini, summer squash and tomato vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat the oil in a saute pan and saute the onion and garlic together until limp (5 to 7 minutes).
Add the lemon juice and basil.
Oil a casserole and layer in the squash, tomatoes and onion mixture, ending with the tomato on top. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Remove the cover.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from bones; set aside. Cook spaghetti in 2 quarts chicken broth until done.
Dice green pepper, onion and garlic and saute in oleo.
Add diced celery, mushrooms and tomatoes.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add to chicken and spaghetti.
Put in baking dish so it will be about 2 1/2 inches deep.
Cover with grated cheese and bake for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Open
baked potatoes.
Fill with meat, desired stuffing items (some or all of listed) and picante sauce.
Heat together Velveeta,
milk
and
1/2 cup picante sauce.
Enjoy!
Serve with mixed green salad, fruit salad and a light dessert.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, salt, butter or margarine and flour (dissolve flour in a little water first) and the rest of the water and vinegar together.
Cook over hot water, about 25 minutes. Cool a few minutes to luke warm.
Pour filling into the unbaked pie crust and bake in 425° oven until the pastry is nicely browned.
Beat the egg whites, add a tablespoon of sugar per egg and flavor with lemon juice.
Beat until the whites form a peak meringue.
Brown lightly in a 325° oven.
The use of the meringue is optional.

title: summer coolness
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts thoroughly and press in square or oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip and put on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk and add third layer.
Top with other half of Cool Whip.
Add nuts if desired.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix and bake in 2 greased cookie sheets at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: angel pie a la gloria
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add all ingredients, except sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Put in deep buttered 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Crust should be high and slightly browned.
Turn off oven.
Let cool with door open.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Make this in the crock-pot at low setting.
Open all ingredients and just dump in the crock-pot.
Can be made in under 10 minutes. Tastes like homemade!
Mix before going to work and it will be ready when you come home.
Enjoy.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Let rolls rise.
Press rolls down flat with slice of pepperoni.
Top with cheese and fold.
Roll up and close ends. Place rolls on greased baking sheet and bake until light brown at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until transparent.
Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry glaze
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch into drained juice; cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.
Add food coloring and cherries; cool and pour on top of dessert.
Chill to serve.

title: caramel finger bread
directions: Put frozen balls in well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over dough balls.
Make syrup with remaining ingredients and pour over dough.
Let set at room temperature overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: macaroni special
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Cook mushrooms until tender. Grate cheese.
Drain peas.
In a large Pyrex bowl alternate a layer of macaroni, cheese, peas, mushrooms and sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper, leaving macaroni, cheese and crumbs on top of last layer.
Pour 1 can tomato juice on top, then pour cream and 1 cup tomato juice over all.
Cook slow 4 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread ingredients in pan in the order listed but do not stir anything together.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan. Place fruit on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barboursville almond macaroons
directions: Place almond paste, sugar and lemon juice in a mixing bowl. Add 8 unbeaten egg whites and mix to form a soft dough.
Add the remaining egg white only if necessary.
Using a teaspoon, drop the dough onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pimento dip
directions: Cook egg yolks, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Add oleo and let cool, then add onion, cream cheese and jar of pimentos. Refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: dusty rice
directions: Brown hamburger in large frying pan; drain off grease.
Chop onion, pepper and garlic; toss in with meat.
Add Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Cook for a minute.
Cover and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: quick cocoa
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in a mug; add enough milk to make a thin paste.
Mix until smooth.
Add milk to fill mug.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High or until steaming.
Makes 1 serving.

title: almond bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Beat until mixture reaches dough-like consistency.
Spread in bottom of greased pan. Combine remaining 2 eggs, vanilla, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top of cake mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with almonds and bake 30 minutes more or until firm.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: fudge brownies(for serious chocolate brownie lovers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and turn upside down.
Mold a piece of foil, shiny side down over bottom of pan.
Turn over pan and place foil in pan.
Place one tablespoon of butter in pan and put in oven to melt.
Spread butter over foil after melted.

title: shaker corn pudding
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir in corn and milk.
Pour ingredients into a buttered casserole and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir once halfway through cooking. When done, pudding will be golden brown and a knife inserted will come out clean.

title: pistachio pound cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and put aside.
In a saucepan over low heat, mix remaining ingredients.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Add 1/2 of saucepan mixture to each pan.
Add 1/2 of cake mix/pudding mixture to each pan.
(This mixture will not spread evenly, but it will rise and fill loaf pan completely during baking.)
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 300°.
Cool completely before removing.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Blend until smooth.
May add a little onion.
Some milk may be needed if mixture is to thick.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Put all above ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly. Roll into balls (about walnut size). Refrigerate - the colder the better-easier to dip.

title: denver sandwich
directions: Mix well and fry in skillet until eggs are done.
Cut and serve on 2 slices bread as a sandwich.
Very good.

title: grandma dee's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs, milk, and oats.
Stir together flour, salt, soda, and cinnamon.
Add slowly.
Last, stir in chocolate chips or other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
This is my favorite "memory" recipe of my Florida grandmother.

title: feather hot rolls
directions: Add the
2 beaten eggs to the cooled milk mixture.
Add this to the yeast mixture and add the 4 cups of flour.
Knead. Refrigerate
overnight.
Form
into individual rolls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate syrup pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add chocolate
syrup and sugar; beat until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time and continue to beat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured pan.
Start in cold oven.
Do not open door for 1 hour.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until done.

title: grandma's raisin bread
directions: Boil all ingredients together until margarine is melted.
Then turn stove off and add 3 level teaspoons baking soda.
Stir and let this cool for about 4 hours or more.
Add flour.
Pour into desired pans, either loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: In a medium pot, place water,

salt and rice. Cook on stove top on high until rapid boiling. Turn down to low and simmer with lid on for 15 to 20 minutes until water is gone. Place aside. In a large skillet on medium heat, warm the oil and then add the rice and bacon, stirring constantly. Fry the rice for 5 minutes. Add eggs (stirring fast to avoid large pieces of eggs). After eggs are stirred in, add the pepper, chicken, carrots and peas. Cook on low, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes. Add 4 to 8 tablespoons of soy sauce depending on taste. Serves 3 to 5 people.

title: potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cool slightly; stir in flour.
Add milk a little at a time.
Stir to mix well.
Pour over potatoes.
Add salt and pepper, then cheese.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cook pudding according to package; add cake mix (dry) and oil. Mix with mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: honey drumsticks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle drumsticks with salt and pepper. Place in baking dish and cook 20 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Salt ribs.
Place in shallow roasting pan, meaty side up. Roast in very hot oven (450°) for 30 minutes.
Drain excess fat from pan.
Top each piece of ribs with a slice of unpeeled lemon and a slice of onion.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and pour over ribs.
Lower temperature to 350°; bake until well done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste ribs with sauce every 15 minutes.
If sauce gets too thick, add more water.

title: sugar cookies(rolled)
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla and cream well.
Then add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Chill for 10 minutes.
Roll and cut into desired shape. Bake at 400° until very light brown.
May be frosted with granulated sugar, if desired or just left plain.

title: sachertorte cookies
directions: Beat butter and pudding until fluffy; beat in egg.
Add flour gradually.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and make thumb imprint.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Remove; cool and fill each imprint with 1/2 teaspoon preserves. Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Drizzle 1/2 teaspoon over each cookie.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook until tender.
Add meat and vegetables to chicken broth and cook until all vegetables are tender.
Add noodles and soups.
Cook over low heat until noodles are done.

title: st. james coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and spices together.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse corn meal.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Add to dry mixture in halves, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Soften gelatin in water; let stand 5 minutes. Drain pineapple; reserve juice. Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Place juice in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Add gelatin mixture and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar, lemon juice and cream cheese, using a wire whisk to blend. Chill until partially set. Fold in pineapple chunks, orange, coconut and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce and garnish with lemon slices.

title: lemon cream pie(8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom and sides of 9 inch pie plate.
Bake for 8 minutes or until golden.
Let cool completely on wire rack. Combine sugar, cornstarch, and salt in saucepan and gradually stir in water and low fat buttermilk.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute or until thick, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of the hot mixture into egg substitute and add to the remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, and stir in 2 tsp. grated lemon rind and fresh lemon juice.
Spoon lemon mixture into prepared crust.
Cover surface of pie with plastic wrap and chill.
Spread whipped topping over filling just before serving.
Garnish with lemon zest, lemon rind curls, lemon slices and mint - if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix with broccoli and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake uncovered 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll crackers very fine.
Mix with margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbs.
Keep 1/2 cup for top. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; set aside.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and Eagle Brand milk in top of double boiler. Mix nuts with mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Let stand in refrigerator for 15 minutes or longer.
Melt chocolate morsels and paraffin.
Dip candy and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: diet soup
directions: Mix together the ingredients and add basil, oregano, thyme and garlic powder to taste.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 hour.

title: chocolate cloud cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add prunes, vanilla, eggs or Egg Beaters and skim milk.
Stir until blended.
Combine coffee and boiling water.
Stir into batter until blended.
Pour batter into two 9-inch pans or one oblong pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick inserted in center.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Mix pineapple with fruits which have been cut up.

title: marinade for meat to be grilled
directions: Marinate
pork
chops,
chicken, seafood or whatever in the Italian dressing for several hours before cooking.

title: down east fish chowder
directions: Let fillets thaw.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix milk, cream and saltines; set aside.
Cook onion and celery until soft.
Cook carrots and potatoes also (nuke in microwave).
Add broth to vegetables.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add fish, saltines and milk mixture; also add butter or oleo.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes, or until fish flakes. Salt and pepper.

title: angel hair pasta
directions: Cook all ingredients in butter and oil, except pasta and cheese.
Salt to taste.
Cook angel hair pasta in salted water according to package; drain and mix with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: aunt rene's seven-up salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and refrigerate to gel.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Spread 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Drizzle over cake and sprinkle on chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rest of batter by teaspoon on top.
Bake again at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cake will be moist.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together, alternately with buttermilk.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in blackberry jam.
Blend in raisins and nuts which have been dredged in small amount of flour.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased and lightly floured 8-inch square layer pans.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine the soup and cream cheese.
Heat until smooth. Dissolve the gelatine in the water. Add to soup and chill until slightly thickened. Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased mold and chill several hours.
Remove from mold and serve with Town House crackers or other crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well. Form into a loaf. Place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix 1/2 cup ketchup with 1/4 cup brown sugar and top meat loaf. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until done in the center.

title: yummy cake
directions: Bake a white cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix instant pudding and pour over cooled cake.
Whip the whipping cream and add pineapple to whipped cream.
Pineapple must be well-drained. Spread mixture over pudding and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in large skillet.
Drain. Add 1 can corn, tomato sauce and ketchup.
Let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Then put into a large casserole dish.
Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake until the biscuits turn brown.
Bake at the temperature on the biscuit can.

title: homemade chicken pie
directions: Cook and cube chicken breast.
Mix with vegetables and soup. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into deep-dish pie shell. Cover with pie crust.
Pinch together to seal and cut slits in top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It will be brown and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar until creamy, then add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and flavoring.
Bake in a tube pan 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil
eggs, dice and
set
aside.
Boil
chicken
until done, cool.
Cut chicken into small strips or pieces.
In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, mix
chicken, cream of celery soup, 1 can water and eggs.
Stir
thoroughly.
Using
biscuit
mix of your choice, place biscuits side
by
side
on
top of chicken mixture.	Bake at 375° until biscuits are done.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in souffle dish and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk.
Form into crust.
Spread and press mixture into lightly oiled pie dish.
Slice tomatoes into crust. Sprinkle basil, salt and pepper over the tomatoes.
Spread mayonnaise over tomatoes.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mayonnaise. Bake in 375° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until crust has browned.
Bacon bits may also be added along with the basil and salt and pepper.

title: baked coconut pie
directions: Stir together well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers the long way and layer with sliced onion, dill and garlic (as much as you desire).
Put in an ice cream pail. Pour cooled brine over pickles.
Let stand 4 to 5 days in refrigerator.
Store in fridge, covered.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook celery and onions in chicken broth a short time; celery and onions should be slightly crisp.
Add cut up chicken, molasses beads and La Choy sauce. Mix well.
Add sliced water chestnuts and mix in. Do not overcook and do not put in too much broth or the chop suey will be too soupy.
Serve with rice or Chinese noodles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a big bowl.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Keep cold until serving.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Cook the onions slowly in the butter and oil in the covered saucepan for 15 minutes or longer.
Uncover; raise heat to moderate and stir in the salt and sugar.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes stirring frequently until the onions have turned an even, deep, golden brown.
While cooking, sprinkle in the flour and stir for 3 minutes.
Away from heat, blend in the boiling liquid.
Add the wine and season to taste.
Simmer partially covered for 30 to 40 minutes or more, skimming occasionally.
Correct seasoning.
Set aside uncovered until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, return to simmer.
Just before serving, stir in the cognac (if desired). Pour into a soup tureen or soup cups over the rounds of bread. Sprinkle cheese on top of soup.
(Instead of pouring soup over bread rounds, bread may be place on top of the soup before cheese is added.)
Servings for 6 to 8.

title: simmered short ribs
directions: Marinate beef short ribs in soy sauce overnight.
Roll ribs in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil in heavy roaster.
Add onion slices, water, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 4 hours. Add water, if necessary.
Good with rice.

title: zucchini beef
directions: Mix meat, shredded zucchini and bread crumbs.
Form into 8 1/2-inch patties.
Brown on both sides in a large nonstick skillet. Stir in sliced zucchini and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, turning patties and stirring 2 or 3 times until zucchini is tender.
Add potatoes and simmer 3 minutes longer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Then top with 2 cups of crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/4 cup of melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(If hash browns are frozen, you may need to leave in the oven a little longer.)

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, saute onions in oil until tender.
Drain all liquid from spinach and add to cooked onions in skillet.
Add cottage cheese, cream cheese, Feta cheese, dill, pepper and egg and mix well.
Remove half of phyllo sheets from package; keep the rest wrapped in plastic wrap or a wet tea towel to keep from drying out.

title: low fat cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy, gradually adding eagle brand milk, until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust. Chill 4 to 5 hours or until set. Top with favorite fruit or pie filling. I refrigerate my fruit or pie filling also before adding it to pie.

title: no crust cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine ingredients.
Beat and pour into greased 8 or 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Can top with cherries or blueberries.

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine ground beef, tomato sauce, 2 eggs and bread crumbs; mix well.
Shape into 1 loaf; place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Pour remaining meat loaf fixin's on top of loaf to coat and bake 15 minutes longer. Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange pineapple tea
directions: Place water in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Add tea bags. Remove from heat and let steep for 3 minutes.
Combine sugar with 2 cups or water and bring to a boil, in a sauce pan.
Add cloves and boil for 10 minutes, stirring often, until syrupy.
Add syrup to tea.
Mix in juices.
Strain and serve hot.
Yields 2 gallons.

title: dutch-style beef and cabbage(crock-pot)
directions: Trim fat off beef and cut into cubes.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat with mixture.
In skillet, quickly brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Drain off fat.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Add onions to skillet.
In same skillet, combine water, vinegar and bouillon granules.
Stir together, scraping browned bits from skillet.
Pour into crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours. Serve beef over cooked cabbage.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients in large container.
Store in covered container (ice cream pail works great).
Add 1/2 cup mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Use coffee mug.
Add marshmallows.
You may microwave water for three minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Add margarine to crushed cookies.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in freezer and freeze.
Spread ice cream over frozen cookie crust.
Put back in freezer.
When frozen, spread peanuts and fudge over top; freeze.
Add Cool Whip; freeze.
Ready to serve after Cool Whip freezes.

title: inside-out chocolate bundt cake
directions: Combine pudding, cake mix, chips, milk and eggs in a bowl. Mix by hand for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Pour into greased Bundt pan that has been floured (12 cup pan).
An angel food pan will also work.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes or until done.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer diced onions in butter.
Mix remaining ingredients and add onions last.
Use for Sloppy Joes or baste on chicken.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Combine ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight. Roll and shape like strawberries.
Roll in red sugar.
Color slivered almonds green and use as stems or you can use decorator bag and leaf tip with powdered sugar icing.

title: paprika chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika.
Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
In baking dish 13 x 9-inches in 425° oven, melt butter or margarine.
Remove baking dish from oven.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin-side down, in single layer in butter or margarine in baking dish.
Bake 25 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over; bake 15 minutes longer or until chicken is golden and fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and mash.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise, onions, egg, salt, pepper and half of the butter. Place in casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs, cheese and rest of butter.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato and hamburger casserole
directions: Put a little milk in bottom of casserole to keep potatoes from sticking. Salt and pepper to taste. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all excess fat from steak and cut into 3-inch strips, about 1/2-inch wide.
Combine 1/2 cup flour, the salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Toss with steak strips to coat thoroughly.
Place coated steak in crock-pot.
Stir in onion rings and mushrooms. Add beef broth.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Before serving, combine sour cream with 1/4 cup flour.
Stir into crock-pot.
Serve stroganoff over noodles. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: cheese in puff pastry(servings:  4)
directions: Split crescent rolls in half.
Wrap rolls around cheese.
Seal cheese tightly.
Beat egg white (you can cheat and use the whole egg) and brush over the top of the rolls.
Bake according to roll recipe (usually 375° for 11 to 13 minutes, until crust is golden. Cheese may run if not fully sealed.)
Let everyone cut into wedges.

Don't forget to take the cheese out of the wax coating! The nice thing with Edam and Gouda is that they come in various flavors, smoked, with caraway seed to name two and this gives you more variation.

title: vegetable-rice soup
directions: Heat olive oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onions; saute about 5 minutes or until slightly browned.
Add carrot and celery; saute about 3 minutes. Add broth, water, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until carrot is tender. To pack in lunch, add 1/2 cup cooked rice and pour into wide-mouth thermal container.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix crumbs with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan dish.
Cook onions in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender (not brown).
Put in pie shell.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over onions.
Put cheese on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into wedges.
Better served warm.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shell. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: butter brickle torte
directions: Mix crackers and melted margarine; pat into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pie filling and milk.
Add ice cream and Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Crush 15 crackers over top.
Freeze; cut into squares.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Beat butter for 30 seconds; add 2 cups sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Form dough into 1-inch balls; roll in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Place balls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet; flatten slightly.
Bake in 375° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 66 cookies.

title: heath bars
directions: Bring butter, margarine and sugar to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Spread graham crackers over a cookie sheet and place slivered almonds (or nuts of your choice) over graham crackers and put in oven for 5 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks with half the sugar; add melted oleo.
Mix other half of sugar with cocoa and flour.
Add a little hot water (3 tablespoons) only enough to dissolve.
Put the two mixtures together and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and vanilla.
The mixture will seem thin.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake until firm, about 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool and cover with Redi Whip or meringue made from beating 3 egg whites until holds a peak.
Add 4 tablespoons white sugar and beat until firm.
Spread from outside edge to crust edge.
Brown lightly in oven for 15 minutes.

title: chef's salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cover and chill. Pour Thousand Island dressing over vegetable mixture; toss gently to coat.
Top with ham and remaining ingredients.
Serving size: 1 1/2 cups.
Calories:
Yields 8 servings.

title: yellow fruit punch
directions: Mix well and chill.
May add ginger ale if you wish.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of flour in bowl with raisins, dates and nuts.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add Karo, lemon and alternate eggs with flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat 5 minutes with electric beater.
Pour mixture over fruit and nuts, then add cherries and pineapple.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Dump into greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mix.
Sprinkle walnuts over cake mixture.
Melt butter.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Preheat
oven
to
In a large bowl, mix together vegetables, roast beef and soup.
Spoon mixture into a 2 quart baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes.
Meanwhile in a small bowl, mix biscuit
mix and water with fork to make soft dough.
Increase oven
temperature to 400°.	Remove casserole.
Top with spoonfuls of dough.
Return to oven.	Bake for 10 minutes.

title: loretta gosik's banana cake
directions: Mash bananas and then add eggs and butter.
Sift all dry ingredients together, then add to banana mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Enjoy, I hope!

title: frosty strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually add ice cream, stirring until melted.
Chill until thickened, but not set (15 to 25 minutes).
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into pastry shell. Chill until firm (20 to 30 minutes).
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: quiche
directions: Add a small amount of flour to milk and add to egg mixture. Bake 1 (9-inch) pie crust at 375° for 10 minutes or until begins to "puff up."
Mix cheeses.
Spread 1/2 of cheese mixture in bottom of shell.
Layer 3/4 cup of any mixture over cheese.
Add remaining cheese.
Pour basic custard over entire pie.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Spray large pot with Pam.
Add chicken pieces and brown.
Add broth, water and the rest of the broth ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes over low heat, uncovered.

title: eggplant with spice!
directions: Heat oil in large frypan or wok.
Add garlic and chili sauce. Stir-fry for 30 seconds over medium-high heat.
Add cubed eggplant and stir-fry until soft.

title: frozen corn
directions: Cut
corn
from cob.
Mix ingredients.	Bring to a boil and let
simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool overnight,	so all liquid is absorbed in kernels.
In morning, pack and freeze.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Prepare a pie pan by buttering it well.
Put milk and sugar into a 2 or 3-quart pan.
Stir with a wooden spoon until sugar is absorbed into the milk.
Place on low heat and cook slowly, stirring very little, until a few drops dropped into cold water make a soft ball.
Remove from fire.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until mixture starts getting thick; pour into prepared pan and spread.
Cut before it hardens too much.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce.
Blend well.
Add nuts, raisins and zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done when tested with toothpick.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: saucy pheasant
directions: Salt, pepper and flour cut up pheasant as for fried chicken. Brown in small amount of cooking oil.
When well browned, add the soup and water and cover.
Cook until well done at a simmer for about 45 minutes or put in oven at 325°.

title: saw dust pudding
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice.
Add the pineapple to jello and water.
Stir.
Put miniature marshmallows over top and let set and jell.
In a saucepan put sugar, flour, juice, then egg.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Let them cool.
Pour over jello that has already jelled.
Whip Dream Whip and stir in cream cheese.
Spoon over top of jello and then sprinkle nuts over top.

title: crunchy topped squash casserole
directions: Wash and trim squash.
Cook squash and onion in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Combine squash, sour cream, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, margarine and paprika; sprinkle over squash mixture.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sour creamed sugared nuts
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar in pan.
Heat to 223°, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir rapidly until mixture has coated nuts. Spread on tray (wax paper).
Separate and let cool.

title: main fish stew
directions: Saute the first 5 ingredients in kettle for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and wine. Cook 5 minutes more. Add next 6 ingredients and simmer, covered, for 25 minutes. Add cod fillets and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes more. Top with parsley. Bottled clam juice can be substituted for fish stock.
Pollock, haddock or hake fillets can be substituted for cod. Serves 4.

title: burnt sugar pie
directions: Mix beaten egg yolks (save whites for meringue), sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and enough milk to mix well.
Melt 6 tablespoons sugar in large skillet.
Add rest of milk.
As soon as sugar is dissolved in milk, add other mixture and cook until done.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute chopped onion and green pepper in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add ground beef and brown, breaking up meat with fork as it cooks.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in a saucepan over medium heat until transparent.
Add turkey and cook, stirring until light brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup; cook for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Serve over rice and garnish with paprika.
Yields 4 servings.

title: soft doughnuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk; add potatoes (while hot).
Add lard, eggs and flavoring.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt. Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut and fry in deep fryer in oil.

title: cheese and egg casserole
directions: Dice buttered bread; place in bottom of an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Layer bacon and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top is slightly browned.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, orange and apples.
Mix and add 1 cup sugar to 1 cup mixture.
When jello starts to set, put the cranberry mixture in.
Add nuts and celery.
This freezes well.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry chopped onion, minced garlic and hamburger until hamburger is browned.
Drain grease; add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix together and put in 12 greased muffin cups.
Put brown sugar on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashioned cream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and up 1/4 on sides of pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Put over crust and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: creamed chipped beef on toast
directions: In a medium saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Whisk in flour all at once to form a roux.
Whisk in milk, a little at a time, increase heat to medium-high, and cook, stirring, until thickened.
Bring to a boil, stir in beef and cayenne, heat through and serve over toast.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup water and salt to melted margarine.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add to margarine mixture.
Add beaten eggs and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except the vanilla and boil in a heavy pan for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove and add vanilla. Serve warm.
Yields 1 1/2 cups of sauce.

title: emerald salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Cool until slightly set. Combine cucumber and onion; drain well.
Add cottage cheese, mayonnaise and almonds/celery.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Turn into 5 cup ring mold.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: raggedy ann cereal bars
directions: First Layer:
Cream 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar; add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut creamed mixture into 2 cups sifted flour. Press mixture into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with second layer.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix coconut and corn syrup well.
Set aside for 1 hour.
Shape into balls and dip into chocolate or colored chocolate.
Necessary chocolate can be purchased at a craft or candy shop.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Place parchment paper on a baking stone (pizza pan 15-inch).
Pour brownie mix on paper and spread into 14-inch circle.
(Do not bake without parchment paper or batter will run.) Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread over brownie "crust." Top with fruit and nuts.
Melt chocolate and butter together, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over pizza.
Chill.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: ham salad
directions: Grind meat, eggs, pickles, cheese and onion.
Add sugar and dressing as desired.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large kettle, cook salt pork until lightly browned. Remove and set aside. Add onions to drippings. Cook until tender. Return salt pork to pan. Add potatoes, clam liquid, salt and Tabasco sauce. Simmer until potatoes are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Add clams, half and half, milk and margarine. Heat, but do not boil. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate-cinnamon cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine buttermilk and next 3 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until blended.
Spoon into an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray; sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: soyteena
directions: Soak
soy
beans
overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine ingredients and
blend
until smooth.
Remove from blender and add 1 cup cornmeal.
Place in sprayed can and cover.
Place in crock-pot with 1 inch of water.
Steam on high 4 hours.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Chop and add potatoes, carrots, onion, celery, green beans and corn (any or all).
Add garlic salt, celery salt and pepper to taste.
Place all ingredients in a crock-pot on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Turn to low and simmer.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Crumble with a fork the Bleu or Roquefort cheese.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Add and mix, but do not beat the sour cream and buttermilk.
Make as thick or thin as desired.

title: mom's peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and then add peanut butter until melted.
Remove from stove; pour into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Press into cookie sheet. Refrigerate until cool.
Cut.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch baking dish or pan.
Mix together the sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted margarine and stir to blend.
Over top, spoon fresh sweetened fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Good served warm.

title: honey balls
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and dry milk. Mix well and form into small balls. Roll balls in graham cracker crumbs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Fold soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper into broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole dish that has been sprinkled with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Top also with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Feeds 10 or 12 people.

title: fried frog legs
directions: Marinate frog legs in lemon juice, water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper for 1 hour.
Mix 1/4 cup flour and all remaining ingredients in separate bowl for batter.
Remove frog legs from marinade.
Dip in batter, coating thoroughly.
Roll in remaining flour.
Cover and fry in hot fat until tender.
Remove cover and brown lightly.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Measure all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix on low speed of electric mixer, then on high speed for 3 minutes while scraping sides of bowl.
Pour into 3 loaf pans that have been lined with aluminum foil, then greased.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: tuna salad
directions: Stir together all ingredients until well mixed.
Makes 1 1/4 cups or enough for 4 sandwiches.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and cocoa 3 times.
Add alternately to mix with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Do not beat.
Bake in 3 round pans in 250° oven, about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple freeze
directions: Combine sour cream and condensed milk.
Stir in milk and lemon juice.
Freeze in 1-quart refrigerator tray until partially frozen.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Freeze firm.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pineapple glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots in 1 1/2-inch sticks or slice round.
Cook until tender in small amount of water with salt.
Drain.
Add pineapple, orange rind, sugar and butter.
Place over medium heat and occasionally toss lightly until glazed, about 5 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: lela's cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and salt. Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and oats and let stand for 20 minutes. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add oats mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased sheet pan at 275° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt in separate bowl.
Add to creamed mixture.
Put baking soda in water and add last.
Dip onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: lazy cobbler(peach)
directions: Melt
stick
margarine
in 2-quart casserole dish. Heat peaches in saucepan until very hot.
Combine dry ingredients with 1/3
cup
milk
to
make batter which should be thin enough to spread
or
spoon over bottom of baking dish.
(Add more milk if needed.) Pour hot peaches on top of batter.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pan coating
directions: Beat.
Stir in airtight container in refrigerator.
Coat your cake pans before pouring in batter, cakes, brownies, etc.
Will never stick.
Easier than grease and flour.

title: jello jigglers
directions: Completely
dissolve
both
gelatins
in boiling water. Pour into
or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat; set aside.
Mix milk, sour cream, eggs and cornstarch until smooth.
Stir in meat and cheese; salt and pepper.
Pour in thawed pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, add cold water and chill until partially set.
Then add pudding and beat 2 minutes with mixer. Chill until mixture mounds when spooned.
Fold in celery, apples, and nuts.
Pour into 7 - 8 cup molds.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Serves 10 -12.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops well on both sides (medium-high) about 15 to 20 minutes.
Turn heat to low and add water; cover with lid.
Cook 45 minutes; turn often.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Let cheese set to room temperature.
Finely chop onions and beef.
Mix 1/2 of chopped dried beef, finely chopped onions and Accent with cream cheese.
Make a ball with cheese mixture.
Roll in remaining half of dried beef.
Serve on Town House crackers.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and butter.
Add soup, pumpkin, milk, nutmeg and pepper.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add stuffing.
Place half of this mixture in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over stuffing in baking dish.
Then top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and line 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans with foil.
Grease foil.
Combine all ingredients, except flour, zucchini and walnuts in large mixing bowl.
Beat about 2 minutes until blended, scraping bowl often.
Fold in flour until blended, then fold in zucchini and walnuts.

title: fishermans chowder
directions: In saucepan, fry bacon until crisp. Remove and set aside. In drippings, saute onion and garlic until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients except fish. Simmer 10 minutes. Add fish and simmer another 10 minutes. Makes 6 cups.

title: red and green pepper slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, peppers and pickles in a large bowl. Toss well.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In a 2-quart saucepan add browned meat, garlic and pepper.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes (I liquefy them in the food processor), tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles 8 minutes; drain.
Spray a glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam. Pour 1/3 of sauce mixture in dish.
Cover with lasagna noodles. Add grated Mozzarella cheese over noodles and spoon Ricotta over cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce and top with Parmesan cheese (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes and serve.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions, garlic salt, oregano, salt and pepper. Mix in all sauces.
Let noodles be cooking in salted water.
In casserole dish, layer noodles, 1/2 meat mixture, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Make second layer of noodles, meat mixture, cheeses, etc.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 easily.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, milk and egg yolks in saucepan.
Heat slowly to a boiling stage, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla and cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until brown.
For meringue, take egg whites you reserved and beat in 2 teaspoons sugar for each egg white until stiff.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into casserole dish.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Lay bacon on top of beans and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar.
Mix in juice, then egg yolks. Pour into boiling water.
Stir well and cook over low heat until thick, about 5 to 10 minutes.
After mixture thickens, stir in butter and rind.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: cherry glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread over ham before baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Arrange in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix rice, soup (undiluted), onion, milk and cheese.
Spread over broccoli and cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: blender lemon cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, brown sugar and butter.
Pat into 9-inch cheesecake pan or 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine in blender:
cottage cheese, honey, yolks, salt, peel and lemon juice, vanilla and yogurt.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; gradually add sugar and beat stiff.
Fold in cheese mix until blended.
Turn into prepared crumb pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250°. Turn off oven; leave in oven 1 hour longer.
Cool and chill.

title: two minute waltz cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients.
Boil, stirring occasionally, 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in the next 5 ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop in food chopper the cranberries, orange, pecans and pineapple.
Add sugar; let set 1 to 2 hours.
Add gelatine to cold water.
Set for 15 minutes.
Mix raspberry gelatin and boiling water.
Add all together and pour in dish.
Refrigerate and let set.

title: spaghetti and meatballs for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and add enough water to moisten.
Shape into small balls and place in a single layer in a large baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Melt butter in round cake pan.
Stir in parsley, dill seed, onion and cheese.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Cut each biscuit in half.
Dip in butter mixture and turn once, coating well.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: linzer torte
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves into medium-size bowl.
Cut in butter.
Stir in egg, almonds, Kirsch, lemon rind and juice until mixture is well blended.
Chill 1 hour, or until dough gets firmer.
Cut the dough in half and press half to fit bottom of a 10-inch greased and floured spring-form pan.
Spread 1/2 cup of jam over dough. Sprinkle a pastry board lightly with flour and roll finger thick strips of dough.
Arrange strips, lattice fashion, over preserves. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until pastry is firm.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Remove cake from pan.
Fill lattices with additional raspberry jam, if you wish.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mae's friendship loaf
directions: Beat by hand the eggs, oil and sugar.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and powder. Add dry to wet, mixing well by hand, alternating with the apples.
Spray Pam on pans and pour evenly in 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients; form into patties.
Fry in hot oil until done.

title: quick cobbler (no fool) pie
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch baking dish. Combine flour, sugar and about 1/2 of the milk. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Add remaining milk and stir until smooth. Pour batter over melted margarine, but do not mix. Sprinkle drained fruit over top, but do not stir. Bake for 30 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: frozen candy bars
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Line shallow 9 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Spread mixture evenly.
Freeze.
Cut into equal servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs; beat well.
Add sour cream, nutmeg and cream of tartar; beat well.
Add flour.
Roll out and cut.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes. These cookies do not brown.

title: quick casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish broccoli, turkey or chicken, rice and mushrooms. Mix together soups, milk, mayo, paprika, salt and pepper. Pour mixture over layers in casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees. Take out and add 1 cup cheese and can of shoe string potatoes. Bake for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: elegant raspberry chocolate pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Spoon in ice cream, stirring until melted and smooth.
Chill until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients except egg whites.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and roll into balls (shooter Aggie size).
Melt together the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls, leaving tops undipped.
Lay on waxed paper.

title: randi's chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in Bundt pan in 325° oven for 70 minutes or until done.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Cream margarine and sugar, add flour mixture.
Stir in frosted flakes.
Drizzle melted chocolate chips over dough and swirl gently through mixture.
Drop by Tbsp. on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 for 12 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and creamy. Add mashed bananas and mix well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and baking soda alternately with the sour cream.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter well, add sugar gradually, continue to mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each, then add sour cream. Sift dry ingredients, and add gradually to mixture.
Stir in flavoring; pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Be careful not to overcook; cake is better moist.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Place cabbage in greased casserole.
Cover with onion, beef and rice.
Mix soup, water and seasonings and pour over all.

title: tony's all-purpose creole seasoning
directions: Mix well and use as you would salt.
If too peppery, add more salt to mixture.
Then season to taste.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Mix spinach with yogurt and soup mix. Serve with whole grain crackers.

title: drop tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Blend well and add vanilla. Mix flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture and blend.
Drop with soup spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
Cool and store in cookie jar.
They keep for weeks.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown meat; do not drain.
Cook noodles.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 meat, 1/2 kraut and 2 cans soup.
