Repeat a second layer using all the meat brownings, ending with soup.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours uncovered.

title: sweet vidalia onion cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan with Baker's Joy (two 9-inch round pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan).
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in large bowl.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Place chunk chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Spread green beans over chicken.
In a saucepan, melt margarine; add onion and saute.
Add mayonnaise, soups and cheese; stir over medium heat until cheese is melted.
Spread mixture over green beans.
Bake in a preheated 325° to 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle French fried onions over casserole; return to oven until onions brown.
Yield 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Mix in broth as much as you need and mix together.
Let your broth come	to
a
boil while rolling out your dumplings. Cut in small
pieces
and	drop
in
broth.
Let
cook
slow; continue until
you	roll all of your dumplings.
Cut and drop in your broth to cook.
Add the black pepper.
Let cook slow, about 30 minutes.

title: salt sour dill pickles
directions: Wash and spear cukes.
Place cukes in jars along with dill and garlic buds.
Combine vinegar, water and canning salt.
Bring this mixture to boil.
Pour over cukes in jars and place on hot lids and rings.
(You can reduce salt if desired.)

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Remove cake from oven.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips and nuts.
Pour caramel mixture over entire cake.
Top with remaining batter. Return to oven another 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and butter together and boil over direct heat for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool in pan or sink of cold water. Beat rapidly until it loses its gloss. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish and when cool, cut in squares. Yields about 24 pieces.

title: better than mounds
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in balls.
Taking a few out at a time, keeping rest cold, dip in melted chocolate.
Put on waxed paper.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil
in
large kettle until transparent. Push to one side.
Add ground turkey and cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Add
remaining
ingredients,
except
canned milk.
Stir well.
Cover.
Bring
just
to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes
or until potatoes are tender.
Just before serving, remove from
heat
and
slowly
stir in canned milk.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: corn bread waffles
directions: Mix corn bread as you normally do, but cook it in a waffle iron, when you take it out of the iron, spray tops with a butter spray. Serve hot. Kids love this.

title: delicious apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in buttered dish (pie plate).
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly. Press mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until the top is brown.
Serve warm with ice cream for an added treat!

title: spicy sauerkraut balls
directions: Pat excess moisture from sauerkraut with absorbent paper towels.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in ungreased, shallow baking pan in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen sauerkraut balls.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Spray pie pan.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: country baked chicken
directions: In Dutch oven, spread rice; cover with onion soup mix.
Place chicken on top.
In medium bowl, mix cream of mushroom soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Remove chicken; stir seasoned rice and serve.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Place chicken and meats into pot and cover with water; add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until very tender.
Remove meat from bones and return to broth.
Add all of the other ingredients and cook slowly
until it is as thick as you like, usually about an hour.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
More seasoning may be added, if desired.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Layer in a 8x11 in. baking dish in the order listed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: johnston's temptation
directions: In an oblong baking dish, layer potatoes, onions and anchovies three times.
Add pepper to each layer.
Add heavy cream to mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: luscious banana cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, salad oil and orange juice; mix well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla and mashed bananas.
Beat on high for 5 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Use angel cake pan.)
Frost with whipped cream and garnish with strawberries.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend in with milk; add nuts.
Chill 3 hours; form in 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: jumer-like cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick, water and softened yeast.
Roll 1/2 of dough to 1/4 inch thick.
Cover with soft butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll, stretching while rolling.
Cut in tiny rolls. Dip in melted butter and cinnamon again.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix together green tomatoes, salt and cabbage.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Add to the tomato mixture green peppers, red peppers, onions, vinegar and sugar.
Put the following spices in a cloth bag or a tea ball:
celery seed, mustard seed, cinnamon, whole cloves and turmeric.
Add spice bag to tomato mixture.
Cook until done.
Pour into hot jars.
Seal.
Makes 20 to 22 pints.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix well.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of cupcake liner.
Pour in filling.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Put cherry pie filling on top. Refrigerate.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cook eggplant as in recipe for Fried Eggplant.
Layer in baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese. Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Repeat until dish or pan is full. Bake in 350° oven until cheese is browned.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine half and half, sugar and egg yolks. Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture will coat spoon, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool. Add whipping cream, salt and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into 4 to 5-quart freezer.
Pack with ice and salt (1 cup salt to 5 cups ice cubes).
Crank until firm. Remove dasher.
Drain water off and re-pack with ice and salt (1 cup salt to 4 cups ice).
Crank until ice cream starts to set, about 10 to 15 minutes. Allow ice cream to mellow at least 1 hour in container or in freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat till fluffy. Add milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir in flour, then cherries and pecans. Shape into 7-inch rolls. Roll dough on coconut to coat outside. Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap; chill thoroughly. Cut into 1/4 -inch slices. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees for 12 minutes or until edges are golden.

title: frozen p b j pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip in bottom of pie crust.
Top with grape jam; freeze for 10 minutes.
Mix peanut butter with cold milk until completely blended.
Add pudding with mixer on low speed for 1 or 2 minutes.
Fold in all but 2 tablespoons Cool Whip.
Spoon over jam in pie crust.
Garnish with 2 tablespoons Cool Whip and chopped nuts if desired.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Blend pudding mix into milk.
Stir in condensed milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers in the bottom of a glass bowl (never use a metal bowl) and cover with a layer of bananas, sliced thin (adds more flavor).
Cover with a generous layer of pudding mix.

title: president nixon's braised steaks
directions: In large ovenproof skillet, saute onion in 1 tablespoon of oil until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add thyme.
Set aside. Sprinkle steaks on both sides with seasoned salt and flour.

title: scrumptious meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape into small balls. Place in large skillet with lid.
Cook over a very low flame until meat balls are done.
Drain off grease.
Pour 3 to 4 cups of brown gravy (either homemade or from packets) over meatballs and simmer for at least 30 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes and your favorite vegetable or just as an appetizer.

title: baked herbed fish
directions: Place fish in shallow pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together in bowl.
Grease cake pan with shortening.
Put dough in pan.
Spread out with fingers.
Make sides higher.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put the rolled oats, oil, honey, salt and wheat germ in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over this mixture and cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 teaspoon of honey.
Add to the lukewarm rolled oats mixture.
Sift the powdered milk with the flour and add it cup by cup to the mixture.
Stir thoroughly. When dough begins to get stiff, turn it out onto a floured surface and work in the remaining flour.
Add sunflower seeds and knead into dough.
Put the dough in a greased bowl and let it rise until double in bulk.
Punch dough down, form into two loaves (either round, free-form loaves or in bread pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.
Don't stir.
Add pecans, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tostado pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add seasonings, tomato sauce, tomatoes and bell pepper.
Grease casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips in dish. Add 1/2 meat mixture. Add 1/2 cup cheese. Add rest of chips, then meat.
Place whole chips over meat.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese over chips and place in oven to melt.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Grind.
Mix with 1 cup peanut butter and mayonnaise.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Reserve one artichoke heart and several pimento slices for garnish.
Coarsely chop remaining hearts and pimento.
In medium bowl mix artichokes, pimentos, mayonnaise, green chiles, cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon into shallow 1 1/2 quart dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Cover bottom of greased casserole with crushed cookies. Alternately layer canned fruits (well drained) with crumbs. Sprinkle with brown sugar over top.
Cover with sliced almonds. Pour Kirsch to taste over top and scatter pats of butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 1 hour.

title: butterscotch krispies
directions: Over medium heat, bring Karo syrup and sugar to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over Rice Krispies and mix.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips and melt in top of double boiler. Spread over Rice Krispies.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole(ready to bake in 15 minutes)
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and sides of an 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef in large chunks and drain.
Place beef, broccoli, 1/2 can onions and tomatoes in potato shell.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Cut franks in bite-size pieces.
Add sweet and sour sauce, cherries and pineapple.
Cook 5 hours on high in crock-pot.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes together in a large bowl. Add potatoes.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Top with 1 package cracker crumbs or potato chip crumbs. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and cook carrots until just soft.
Combine carrots, onions and bell pepper in large bowl.
Mix all other ingredients in blender. Pour this marinade over carrots, onions and pepper. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, cream cheese, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs; stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Form tiny balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in large pot until meat is brown. Drain and add all of other ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes. Sometimes I add 1/2 cup macaroni to this soup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar in hot water until completely diluted. Add pineapple juice and freeze in large container.

title: zucchini with lemon
directions: Saute the zucchini, sliced thin, in 1 tablespoon oil until tender.
Stir in the minced garlic, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook 1 minute.
Add the fresh lemon juice and the grated lemon peel; heat through.
May add some sliced black olives.
Oil-cured olives are very nice.
Serves 4.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Fold other ingredients into gelatine mixture after it begins to set.
Top with chopped celery and bell peppers, chopped real fine, mixed with salad dressing.

title: buttercream eggs
directions: Mix well and shape into eggs.
Place on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper after coating with chocolate.
Let stand until cool.

title: sugar-free chocolate crunch candy
directions: Blend milk and cocoa to make a fine powder.
Stir in sugar substitute and water and beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in chow mein noodles and drop on waxed paper.
Makes 30 candies.

title: virginia's zucchini soup *
directions: Saute onions; add zucchini, basil and stock.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in blender until smooth.
Add milk and season to taste.
Serve hot or cold.
Yield:
6 bowls.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat the last 5 ingredients together.
Combine the two mixtures and stir.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch or Bundt pan). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except nuts and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and pierce cake with fork. Pour glaze over cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp; cut up.
Grate onion.
Mix all ingredients, adding shrimp last.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.
Serve in green pepper cup.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly on tortillas.
Roll tortillas tightly. Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut rolls into 1-inch pieces.
Discard ends.
Serve with spirals face up.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Add salt, vanilla and eggs (one at a time), beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place cake in cold oven and set at 275°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or a little longer until nice and brown.

title: amaretto coffee
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour in boiling water.
Stir.
Add cream of coconut, almond extract and cream, then stir.
Serve hot.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and dry.
Rub with oil and bake directly on oven rack at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: meatballs in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup. Brown meatballs. Simmer in mushroom soup (do not add the milk). Then put into oven for 1 hour at 300°, uncovered.

title: walnut dill sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a blender container and blend until satin smooth.
Refrigerate in a tightly covered container. Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: Melt fat in large skillet.
Add sugar.
Stir until brown.
Add onion and cook slowly until golden.
Add cabbage, apples, vinegar and seasoning to taste.
Cook very slowly until all ingredients are tender.
Add a little water, if necessary to prevent sticking. Serves 4.

title: frosted fruit salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and cool.
Add pop.
Chill until partially set.
Fold pineapple and banana into jello.
Put into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Combine sugar and flour in saucepan.
Stir in reserved pineapple liquid and egg. Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Chill.
Fold whipped cream into this mixture.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Refrigerate until topping is firm.

title: spinach with two cheeses
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Trim and wash spinach.
Do not dry. Place spinach in large pot with just water that clings to leaves. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until limp for fresh spinach or according to package for frozen spinach.
Drain cooked spinach in colander, pressing out most of the liquid.
Chop spinach fine.

title: spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. Drain off some grease, then add all other tomato ingredients and spices.
Cook on medium to low heat for 2 to 3 hours.

title: apricot cake
directions: Mix together oil and sugar on low speed of electric mixer. Add eggs and sift in all dry ingredients.
Mixture will become very stiff.
Beat in apricot baby food.
Stir in by hand chopped nuts.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake until splits in top are done.
Test for doneness by sticking toothpick in center of splits until it comes out clean.
Top will be a little shiny and crusty.
Serve plain by itself or good with ice cream, fruit or pudding. Makes an excellent birthday cake.
Keeps moist a long time in a closed cake container.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
thoroughly after each addition.
Sift flour and add to creamed
mixture,
one spoonful at a time, alternately with milk. Add vanilla;
stir in crushed pineapple and juice. Blend well. Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan. Place cake in cold oven.	Turn oven to
325°and bake for 1 1/2 hours
or until top springs back
when
touched
lightly.
Let stand for a few minutes in pan.
Run
knife
around
edge
and turn it out.
Put the icing on while hot.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter
and
sugar.
Blend in egg or egg yolks. Sift salt,
baking
powder
and flour together; add to mixture. Blend in
vanilla.	Bake
on
lightly greased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: molded fruit salad
directions: Put 1 cup of boiling water, 1 1/2 cups cold water and juice from fruit in Jell-O.
Add cottage cheese and mix.
Add fruit cocktail, bananas and marshmallows; fold in the whipped cream with a fork.
After your 1 cup is whipped, it will be more than 1 cup. Add entire amount.

title: edible nests - an easter treat
directions: Heat sugar and Karo syrup until boiling. Stir in peanut butter until melted. Stir in Rice Krispies. Shape into edible nests and fill the nests with jelly beans.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Mix Pepsi and catsup in a skillet.
Add chicken and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to simmer and cover.
Cook for an hour. Uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add egg, sugar and Crisco.
Mix, then add 4 cups flour.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon into muffin tin. Fill halfway up.
Bake at 400° until done.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add ice cream. Stir in oranges, pineapple and walnuts.
Pour in serving dish and chill.

title: pork roast with garlic and rosemary
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth.
Score top with sharp knife.
Make small slashes in several places and insert garlic.
Rub surface with rosemary.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place on a roasting rack in a shallow pan.
Roast at 325° for about 45 minutes per pound.
Allow to rest 10 minutes before carving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach real well.
Mix all the ingredients together. Chill.
Serve with a variety of raw vegetables.

title: fast fudge frosting
directions: Add first 3 ingredients.
Add water, butter and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Frosts one 9 x 13-inch or two 8 or 9-inch cakes.

title: bacon-asparagus quiche
directions: Drain and crumble the bacon.
Set aside.
Brush mustard evenly over bottom and sides of pastry shell.
Bake shell at 375° for 15 minutes or until firm, but not completely browned.
Sprinkle baked crust with the bacon and arrange cooked, drained asparagus over. Sprinkle with half of the Swiss cheese.

title: corn dog twists
directions: Unroll dough into one long sheet and push centers together. Pull strips apart so you have 8 long strips and not 16. Wrap each long strip around a hot dog, twisting from the top down. Put on ungreased cookie sheets with ends of dough tucked under the hot dog. Brush the dough with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 12 to 16 minutes or until the cornbread twists are light brown.

title: oatmeal marguerites
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Blend in rolled oats and nut meats.
Grease tins or put miniature papers in miniature cupcake tins, if possible.
Drop in by teaspoons. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Put in 9-inch deep pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: black bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients together well before adding avocados.
Enjoy.

title: sweet coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Cook for 1 hour on low heat.
Put over hot dogs, hamburgers or French fries.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Pour into 3 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine and oil. Add beaten eggs. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll mixture into small balls. Press these with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool on rack and store in tight tin in the freezer if not used right away.
Makes a lot of light, crispy cookies.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add milk, beaten egg and vanilla.
Mix and add flour, soda and salt; add oatmeal and chocolate chips. Drop onto cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown (8 minutes).

title: norma jane's ice cream
directions: Mix condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into freezer container, then fill to line with chocolate milk.
Crumble butterfingers finely and sprinkle into milk mixture.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Heat soup and add tuna fish (break up the tuna).
Spoon onto toast.
Spoon a small amount of egg on top.

title: lemon lime refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Set aside.
Mix cake and bake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake.
Poke holes in cake (meat thermometer works good) and slowly pour Jell-O into holes; refrigerate cake and prepare topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snappy liverwurst and beer dip
directions: Cream together liverwurst and cream cheese.
Add mayonnaise, Tabasco, horseradish and onion powder; blend.
Gradually stir in beer.
Beat until smooth.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vegetable oil.
Sift together soda, salt and
flour;
add
to
mixture.
Add
pecans,
apples and vanilla. Bake
at 315° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 layers, 1 tube or 1 loaf.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend crumbs and 1/2 cup butter; press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Beat sugar, 1 1/2 sticks butter, vanilla and pineapple juice.
Pour on top of cooled crumbs. Arrange sliced bananas on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with well drained pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake 1/2 the mix for 15 minutes in 13-inch baking dish which has been greased and floured at 350°.

title: three cheese tortellini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Set aside. Saute onion in olive oil and butter until transparent.
Add garlic; saute and stir for a few minutes, being careful not to burn garlic.
Add red wine, simmering for a few minutes.
Then add cream cheese, Parmesan, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes; cut off heat, allow to sit for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: spiced chicken with honey
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine in roasting pan.
Stir in honey, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Remove from heat. Arrange chicken in pan, turning to coat with honey mixture.
Bake 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with honey mixture.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a cake pan.
Add sliced apples.
In skillet, melt butter, brown sugar and cinnamon, then add oatmeal and flour. This will get crumbly.
Let cool.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft).
Shape into walnut size balls.
Place meat balls in a single layer on a wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Freeze until solid.
Then put frozen meat balls in freezer bags and keep frozen until you are ready to cook them.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil fryer until tender and remove meat from bone.
Save broth from cooked chicken.
With a food chopper, grind chicken meat and return to about 3 cups hot broth with hot pepper, black pepper and salt to taste.
Grind onions; add about 2 cups whole milk and margarine to broth and chicken.
Bring chicken and broth to a boil.
Remove from heat, add crackers (crumbled) to thicken the stew.

title: open faced spam sandwiches
directions: Grind Spam, American cheese, onion and green pepper.
Mix this with ketchup, milk and salad dressing/mayo.
Cut buns in half, spread mixture on each half and place on cookie sheet.
Put in a 300° oven for 15 minutes or until heated through and the cheese melts.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour. Press dough evenly over bottom of 12 or 14-inch pizza pan, forming rim along edge.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips; continue to bake for 5 to 8 minutes or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Cool; cut into wedges.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas; sprinkle with lemon.
In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Then add flour and soda sifted together.
Beat well, then add vanilla, pecans and mashed bananas.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Do not overbake!
Turn out on rack to cool.
This freezes well.
Slices without crumbling if you cool several hours or overnight.
In a hurry?
Partly freeze, then cut.

title: spanish delight
directions: Fry meat and onion together and season with salt and pepper to taste.
(Chili powder can be added, if desired.) Cook spaghetti 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven until brown.

title: banana shake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
May be served as breakfast in a glass or with cinnamon toast.

title: diabetic strawberry yogurt mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in custard cup. Place in pan of hot water, heat until dissolved. Puree strawberries and punch concentrate in blender. Stir in yogurt, sour cream and gelatin. Refrigerate until partly set. Beat egg whites with sugar until stiff. Fold into yogurt mixture. Freeze or refrigerate until set.

title: may's syrup "t" cakes
directions: Mix. Roll out on floured surface as thin as desired.
Cut out with cookie cutter.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 400°.

title: zucchini cake (bread)
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy, then add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla and blend lightly.
Then combine dry ingredients and add to egg mixture (don't blend).
Just stir dry ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Grease and flour 2 bread loaf pans.
If pans are small, bake for 40 minutes, using 3 pans.

title: sticky buns
directions: In round baking dish, melt margarine 45 seconds on High.
Stir in sugar, syrup and cinnamon.
Add fruit and nuts and spread evenly.
Arrange biscuits around edge of dish.
Cook on High about 3 minutes just until biscuits spring back when pressed.
Invert dish on plate and let rest 1 minute, then remove dish.

title: butterscotch cream pudding
directions: In a double boiler, combine the first 3 ingredients.
Slowly add the milk. Stir until thick. Cook, covered, 10 minutes. Combine egg yolks and sugar with 1/4 cup mixture.
Mix and return to double boiler.
Cook until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon, 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add Parkay and vanilla. Continue in pie or your favorite dessert bowl.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain fruits - making 2 cups liquids.
Boil and add Jello. Add fruit, refrigerate until congealed.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add sugar and nuts.
Spread on top of salad.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown and crumble ground beef.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Top with onion, salt, pepper and Tater Tots.
Combine soups and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir flour and dry ingredients together; fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel, sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake together; let cool.
Unroll and spread with filling mixture. Roll and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces skin side up in a greased baking dish. Do not overlap.
Blend together the butter, flour, salt and poultry seasoning.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 375° uncovered 20 minutes.
Mix together soup, milk and water.
Pour over chicken and bake 30 minutes more or until chicken is tender.

title: broccoli-cheese mini croissants
directions: Cut broccoli florets into small pieces and steam.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix ground berries and whole orange in sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Dissolve jello in hot water and let stand until it begins to get firm.
Add all ingredients and let jell.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream and half the dressing mix. Mix 1/2 of the dressing mix with the chicken and 1 cup of cheese, black olives and green onions to the mixture. Spoon onto tortillas and roll up. Place seam side down in a baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Pour remaining half of the Ranch dressing over enchiladas. Top with salsa.

title: barbecued black beans and rice
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
Combine with tomatoes, chilies, cumin, barbecue sauce and corn.
Simmer gently over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Ladle rice into deep bowls, then ladle black beans with sauce over top.

title: creamy sweet potato casserole
directions: Strain and mash potatoes.
In a large bowl, mix sweet potatoes, butter, pineapple, sugar, vanilla extract, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Transfer to a greased, 3-quart baking dish.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 9 ingredients.
Fry tortillas, one at a time, in 2 tablespoons of oil, for 5 seconds on each side or until golden.
Add oil as needed.
Drain on paper towels.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in saucepan. Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. Turn heat on low and cook until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and pour in blender. Add 1/4 of the cheese and blend until smooth. Continue adding cheese 1/4 at a time until all is blended. Chill. Store in refrigerator and is better if stored overnight.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube and cook potatoes in boiling water until tender. Drain. Sprinkle with vinegar and sugar. Add celery, onion, olives, salt and celery seed. Fold in mayonnaise and eggs. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet. Saute onion and celery. Add gravy, soup and soy sauce. Bring to a boil. Add pork, bean sprouts, bamboo shoots and water chestnuts. Return to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Combine cornstarch with 1/2 cup cold water and stir until smooth. Add to chop suey and return to boil until thickened. Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, olives and seasoning. Separate crescent rolls into triangles and line pie pan; sealing edges together.
Top with meat mixture.
Spread with sour cream and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve topped with lettuce, tomato and taco sauce.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cook raisins in some water and boil until tender;
drain, saving 1/4 cup of water.
In the 1/4 cup raisin water, add baking soda and vanilla.

title: greatest cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Grease 9-inch or 10-inch spring-form pan with Crisco.
Cover sides of pan with 1 cup of the crumbs to about 1-inch from the top.
Pour the rest into bottom of pan and press down until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: stir-fry tofu salad
directions: Drain the tofu well and press gently to remove any excess moisture. Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Trim the tops and tails from the snow peas.
Thinly slice the mushrooms with a sharp knife. Slice the carrots and celery thinly, cutting with your knife at an angle to produce diagonal cuts.
Trim the green onions and slice them in the same way as carrots and celery.

title: eclair cake
directions: In large bowl mix vanilla pudding according to box directions. Add Cool Whip and blend.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo and layer with whole crackers.
Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, then remaining pudding. Top this with another layer of crackers.
Mix together and pour on top the cocoa, syrup, sugar and milk.
For best results, let set at least 8 hours or overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Simmer celery for 10 minutes with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Mix together with vegetables and celery.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat egg. Add other ingredients. Boil until it thickens.
Good for pimento cheese, etc.

title: oven baked brisket
directions: Saturate brisket with seasonings and sauces.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 6 to 8 hours in covered Dutch oven.

title: family goulash
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
While noodles cook, cook and stir ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in rest of ingredients, cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo 5 minutes on medium heat (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Stir in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Soak eggplant overnight in saltwater. Steam until almost done, about 20 minutes. Drain. Soak white bread and cornbread in milk. Saute onion, green peppers and celery in butter about 15 minutes. Combine bread, eggplant, sauteed vegetables, pimento, eggs and seasonings and mix well. Pour in buttered baking dish and top with cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple and heat until Jell-O dissolves. Refrigerate until cool.
Then add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Add to Jell-O mixture and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add chopped onion and jalapeno to taste.
Salt to taste and simmer for 5 minutes; drain.
Stir in chopped green chiles.
Grate American cheese or Cheddar cheese. Mix cornbread mix and eggs (do not add milk).
Add corn.
Pour 1/2 cornbread mixture into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with meat and onion mixture.
Pour on the Ranch Style beans.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Pour remaining bread mixture over top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice dough evenly and arrange on a pizza pan.
Press dough together so it forms a crust.
Bake according to package directions.
Beat softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream with a mixer until smooth.
Spread over cooled cookie crust.
Arrange fruit slices in a decorative pattern on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with small amount of powdered sugar, if desired.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Add onion and rice. Saute a few minutes. Drain. Add tomato sauce and water. Cook until rice is done.

title: caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease sides and bottom of pans. Flour lightly.
Soften butter to room temperature.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water until tender.
Drain cabbage well.
Place cabbage in casserole dish and place cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted.
Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Cook in microwave until thick.

title: stir-fried chicken pancakes(serves 4)
directions: Place flour in a bowl; break in the egg.
Gradually add the milk, beating to form a smooth batter.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Make Dream Whip as directed, then mix with cream cheese.
Beat well.
Mix in sugar.
Put the cream filling on the crust; cover the cream with the pie filling.

title: rhinelander potato salad
directions: Cook bacon, onion and green pepper until bacon is crisp; drain.
Add to remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Heat 30 minutes at 350°.

title: biscuits and beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet;
drain.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients;
heat until bubbly.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Place biscuits on top of meat and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all together and allow seasonings to set awhile.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes!

title: new fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add molasses.
Add egg substitute; beat well.
Add ginger, cinnamon and flour; mix well.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans that have been sprayed with cooking spray. Batter will be thin.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool; remove from pans.
Stack with applesauce or dried apples between each layer.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into 2 cheese balls and roll in chopped walnuts. Refrigerate.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Cook frozen (or fresh) broccoli until tender. Drain. Place in a 10 x 14 pan for first layer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls using rounded teaspoonful.
Roll balls in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each cookie with a solid milk chocolate candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edges.
Return to oven.
Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer until golden brown.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes into cubes.
Spray the potatoes with light spray.
Mix spices together, coat the potatoes evenly and place on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with light oil spray.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until crispy.

title: monterey chicken casserole
directions: Make the day before serving.
Prepare the stewing chicken; cool and cut into small pieces.
Set aside.
Mix together the seasoned dressing, melted oleo and chicken broth.
Place 1/2 the preceding mixture in bottom of 9 x 12-inch casserole.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Finely chop carrots.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place balls on a Teflon coated baking sheet and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed (drain well).
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salad with honey dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients (except veggies). Allow to sit in refrigerator overnight. When ready to serve, mix well. Toss with fresh veggies. Serve immediately.

title: cucumber hors d'oeuvres
directions: Sprinkle salad dressing mix over cream cheese and mix well. Spread mixture on bread slices.
Peel cucumber and slice thin. Place one slice of cucumber on top of each slice of bread. Sprinkle slices with dill weed.
These taste better if made up several hours ahead, with foil on a tray and refrigerated.

title: quick pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour the melted margarine into an 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and line bottom of pan with crushed pineapple.
In a mixing bowl, sift together the flour, salt and white sugar.
Add the oil and 1/4 cup of the milk. Stir until flour is dampened, then beat 1 minute.
Stir in the baking powder and the remaining milk.
Stir in the unbeaten egg whites and the vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over the crushed pineapple in the cake pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the cake comes out clean.
Remove from oven; cool slightly and invert onto a serving plate. Approximately 290 calories per serving.

title: low-fat fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly; stir constantly until mixture bubbles and thickens.
(Add nonfat dry milk to mixture if needs to be thicker.)
Add Parmesan cheese to taste.
Might want to double recipe.
Pour over cooked fettuccine.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Drain pineapple and pour juice over chops.
Top each piece of meat with pineapple slice.
Cover pan, reduce heat and cook slowly for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove cover and baste for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old fashioned molasses stack cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and mix well. Add milk, molasses and nutmeg.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add flour gradually until too thick to mix with mixer.
Using a spoon stir until stiff enough to pour out onto floured board.
Knead again, taking off enough to make one layer at a time, kneading until real stiff.
Roll out thin.
Cut with a fluted pie pan.
Place layers in cake pan.
Will make 7 layers.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream the sugar and cream cheese together.
Add other ingredients and mix together.
Freeze.
Allow to thaw a few minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, milk and let come to boil. Cook to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: sweet potato cream cheese pie
directions: Mix well until smooth the cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into two pie crusts.
Mix sweet potatoes, egg, vanilla flavoring, flour, melted butter and Carnation milk.
Mix well and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all except last 2 ingredients together.
Top with Ritz crackers and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour until done.

title: chocolate drop cookies(no bake)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to quick boil.
Reduce heat to medium and boil 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball when small amount is dropped into glass of water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, rolled oats and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: gazpacho
directions: In large bowl, stir together tomato juice, vinegar, chives and red peppers.
Stir in tomatoes, cucumbers, green peppers, onion and garlic.
Chill 3 hours or until serving time.
Serve with low sodium croutons.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; beat well.
Beat into eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to oil mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
May be baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring to boil sugar, oil and vinegar.
Cool.
Drain sauerkraut.
Combine sauerkraut and chopped ingredients.
Add mustard seed, poppy seed and celery seed.
Pour cooled mixture over salad and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Stir several times during the day.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Bring sugar, salt, butter, evaporated milk and heavy cream to a boil in a large kettle, stirring constantly.
Begin timing when at a full boil.
Boil steadily for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: italian eggplant casserole
directions: Roll eggplant in flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in oil until tender.
Layer in casserole dish with tomatoes and cheese. Bake in 350° oven until hot and cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese stuffed manicotti shells
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, 2 tablespoons parsley, oregano, sugar and garlic powder.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion together.
Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Simmer 40 to 60 minutes in electric frypan at 220°.
Stir occasionally.
Great for picnics.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups.
In a large bowl, beat egg with juice or milk, oil and vanilla. Stir in flour, sugars, baking powder and salt. Stir in nuts and chopped apple.
Fill cups. Sprinkle tops with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes, until golden.
Makes 12 muffins or 36 miniature muffins.

title: chicken soup with semolena
directions: Put the chicken broth in a saucepan over medium-high heat and add the onion; let it boil for 5 minutes.
Put the semolena in 1/2 cup of water and mix, then add to the chicken broth and mix well to prevent clumping.
Add the salt and cardamon, then simmer for 10 minutes.
Finally, add the chicken meat; let boil for 2 minutes, then garnish with parsley.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put in a buttered casserole.
Cook broccoli and drain.	Mix all other ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Cover with cheese crackers.
Bake at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together the buttermilk, salt, soda, sugar, baking powder and egg.
Add enough cornmeal to make a medium-thick batter.
Melt 1 tablespoon shortening in bottom of baking pan and sprinkle in a little cornmeal.
Brown this in the oven.
Add batter and bake at 375° to 400° until done.

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with nonstick coating.
Melt butter and dissolve sugars in double boiler or in microwave on Low power. Pour cinnamon on a plate and coat both sides of each biscuit with it.
Cut biscuits into fourths and drop into Bundt pan.
After each can of biscuits, press them together lightly in the pan so that Monkey Bread will hold together, then pour a little of the butter-sugar mixture over.
Repeat until all biscuits are used and pour remaining butter over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Cool 2 to 3 minutes and invert on serving plate.

title: brandied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine cornstarch, nutmeg, salt and sugar.
Gradually stir in water; cook until clear, stirring once in a while.
Stir in lemon juice and brandy.
Cook potatoes; peel and slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Place in buttered shallow casserole dish; cover with sauce.
Cover casserole dish; bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting once in a while.
Sprinkle with mini marshmallows, then broil.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: In bowl, mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and butter.
Press 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
In saucepan, mix all remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over the rhubarb. Sprinkle remaining flour/oatmeal mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Cool.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken okra gumbo
directions: Base chicken with mixture of 1/4 cup flour, pepper and salt (optional).
In a heavy skillet, fry chicken in margarine until brown; set aside.
Fry okra, tomato and onion in the same pan with the margarine used to cook the chicken.
Set vegetables aside and reserve 2 tablespoons of fat from pan.
In about a 6-quart kettle, add 1/4 flour to the reserved cooking fat, stirring constantly over low heat until light brown, not burnt.
Add water, pepper and vegetables.
Stir a few minutes.
Add fried chicken.
Cook for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender and coming apart.

title: soda pop cake
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups boiling water; set aside.
Mix and bake cake as directed on package.
While
hot, prick all over cake with fork.
Pour Jell-O over cake, then soda pop.
Refrigerate until cool.
Mix pudding as directed; spread over cake.
When set up, frost with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: hootinanny pancake
directions: 1. Turn oven on to 425 degrees.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie shell. Cover with top crust; crimp edges to seal.
Slit top crust and brush with egg (if desired).
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour over sugar and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into acorn size balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Freeze an hour or overnight.
Melt chocolate with shaved paraffin in double boiler.
Do not have water boiling.
Use toothpick and dip 3/4 of the ball into chocolate.
This gives the appearance of a Buckeye.
Store in container in refrigerator.
Will keep for months.

title: virginia apple cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients with exception of the apples.
Place 1/2 apples in 10-inch deep dish pie plate or 9 x 13-inch casserole which may or may not be lined with a bottom crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar mixture, top with remaining apples, then the remaining sugar mixture.
Dot with butter.
Add top crust and dot with butter.
Make slits in crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla and sugar together with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Put on wax paper.
Melt chocolate chips and shortening together.
Dip ball 1/2 down into mixture and place on wax paper.
Refrigerate until chocolate is hard.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Pour punch and ginger ale together.
Spoon in as much sherbet as desired.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: In a shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken.

title: notched potatoes
directions: Notch a large square out of the top of each potato.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spoon into the potatoes.
Replace the notch.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 425°.

title: cheese-nut appetizers
directions: Combine cheese, butter and sugar.
Combine flour, salt and blend into cheese mixture.
Shape dough into small balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Press pecan halves into each ball and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until slightly browned.
Makes 100 wafers.

title: peanut butter melties
directions: In a large bowl cream together peanut butter, butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour until dough is stiff.
Shape into balls, place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onion and green pepper.
Add catsup, vinegar and sugar.
Mix and bring to a simmer.

title: shrimp boil dinner
directions: In a large roaster half full of water, bring the crab boil, lemon halves, Tabasco and salt to a boil.
Add the new potatoes and onions and boil until the potatoes are tender.
Add corn.
When corn is tender, add the shrimp.
The shrimp are ready when they turn pink.
This will take only a few minutes after the water has come to a full boil again.
Drain and serve.
Yields 10 servings. Preparation time is 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix flour, brown sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Stir in oats; mix well and remove 1 1/2 cups for later.
Press rest into buttered 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
While this is baking, mix softened cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, then milk and vanilla, last lemon juice.
Beat well.
Pour over baked crust and sprinkle reserved mixture over top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 40 squares.
Any left?
Put in refrigerator.

title: surprise sausage barbecue appetizers
directions: Brown sausage according to package directions.
Drain.
In small saucepan, mix together a small amount of grape jelly with the cornstarch.
Blend well.
Add remaining jelly and catsup. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and begins to boil.
Continue to cook and stir one minute.
Pour into serving dish; add sausages and stir to coat. Serve with wooden picks.

title: coffee pot punch
directions: Pour in pot the cranberry juice, pineapple juice and water. In basket, put sugars and cinnamon. Perk as usual.

title: mom's congo bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar; stir until well mixed. Allow to cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, then dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in a 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat and honey bread
directions: Scald milk.
Put in bowl and add hot water.
Beat eggs and add.
Add honey, molasses, salt and oil.
Mix in flour well and let set 2 hours.

title: veggie burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cover burgers with a brown gravy mix (or bread crumbs), mash spoonfuls into heated skillet, using vegetable oil.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix together oil, vinegar, parsley, salt, pepper, sugar and lemon juice in a large bowl.
Add mushrooms and garlic clove; toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate for hours or days.
Remove garlic clove and serve on toothpick.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Beat
eggs
in mixer well. Add sugar, Crisco and margarine. Mix
well.	Add
all dry ingredients, then add vanilla. Measure out
with ice cream dipper or large spoon onto cookie sheet.
Take glass
and press each dipper full down. (Be sure and
dip	bottom of glass into some sugar before pressing the dough down.)

title: stuffed pasta shells(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook shells per directions; drain and set aside. Lightly cover bottom of 9 x 13 baking pan (dish) with spaghetti sauce. Set remaining aside. Combine next 8 ingredients. Mix well and stuff shells with 2 tablespoons cheese mixture. Arrange in dish. Spoon rest of sauce over shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. (Goes well with fresh tossed salad, crusty garlic bread and cold sweet iced tea.) Enjoy.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in frozen hash browns.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream and onions.
Pour over potatoes, don't stir!
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over this; don't stir!
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375°.

title: hearty macaroni salad
directions: Boil, rinse and drain macaroni.
Add your chopped onion and green pepper to macaroni.
Add mustard, celery seed, pimentos, relish, sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir well until all ingredients are mixed thoroughly.
The boiled eggs may be wedged or sliced and used as garnishes or they may be chopped and mixed with the other ingredients.
Salt and pepper are optional.
Chill or refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy.

title: cherry park presbyterian church pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Beat remaining ingredients together and stir all together.
This make three single 10-inch pie crusts.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in chicken broth until tender.
Add ham.
Mix flour with small amount of milk until dissolved, then add remaining milk.
Slowly add milk mixture to broccoli and ham over a low heat.
Stir often.
As mixture begins to thicken, add cheese that has been sliced into several small chunks.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: cheesy fritos with hominy
directions: Heat all ingredients except Fritos, cheese, hominy and onions. After they have boiled, add the hominy and onions and bake in a baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven before the last 10 minutes and add Fritos and cheese.
Return to oven for last ten minutes.

title: soaks sandwiches
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2-quart casserole; add onions, green peppers, and cook 8 minutes in microwave oven on High.
Drain. Add other ingredients except buns.
Cook covered for 15 minutes. Spoon onto bottom half of toasted hamburger buns; cover with top half.

title: golden layer cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Alternate flour and milk, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased pans (two or three 9-inch pans).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: weight watchers pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.

title: chili rellenos won ton appetizers
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine beef, onions, cheese, oregano, cumin, garlic salt and chilies.
Place a spoonful of the meat mixture on each won ton wrapper and follow package directions for folding and sealing.
Deep fry 1 1/2 minutes or until golden. Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Yield: 6 dozen appetizers.

title: baked ziti
directions: Bake ziti noodles according to package directions.
Drain well.
Mix liberally with Italian seasoning.
Mix in spaghetti sauce, using 1/2 jar.
Turn into 8 or 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with meatballs in the remaining sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and marinated oranges.
Mix all ingredients.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Melt butter and pour over crackers. Beat whipping cream until very stiff.
Add sugar and cream cheese. Mix well.
Put on top of crackers and butter.
Put pie filling on top of whipping cream mixture.
Store in fridge.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown 1/2 onion with hamburger; cut up rest of onion and bell pepper.
Cook with beans.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate butter brickle
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Next, place layer of crackers.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, bring brown sugar and butter to boil.
Boil exactly 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour and spread over crackers. Bake 5 minutes.
Remove and spread chocolate chips.
Break up peanut butter brittle and cover chocolate layer.
Freeze until hard.
Remove aluminum foil and break up.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat well with spoon. Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Simmer onion, celery and carrots in 1 cup of stock for 10 minutes.
Add remaining stock, tomato juice and potatoes; cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 10 servings.

title: brown bread
directions: Simmer raisins in water for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool. Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in cooled raisins and water.

title: creamy onion potato soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook 1 minute or until onions are tender.
Gradually add broth.
Add potatoes and next 3 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in milk and heat thoroughly.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chipped beef on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Wrap breasts in bacon.
Put 1 chicken breast on top of each chipped beef slice.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour mixture over chicken. Do not salt.
Cook for 3 hours at 300°.
Cover for the first hour. May also be cooked at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Good served with rice or over toast.
Delicious!

title: sarde salate
directions: Rinse sarde very good.
Clean bones, etc.
Cover with olive oil and add spices.
Can be served cold or lightly fried.
Add crushed pepper to taste (optional).

title: tuna salad mold
directions: Heat soup in pan and add gelatin.
(Make sure gelatin is dissolved.)
Cool and then add sour cream and mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: taco pie
directions: Flatten biscuits in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Add taco mix.
Cut up onion and green pepper; add to meat mixture. Cook 10 minutes on low until thickened.
Spread over biscuits and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup Swiss cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and half of the onion rings.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: hamburger barbecue(barbecue hamburger for a crowd)
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chess cake squares
directions: In a saucepan heat butter and both sugars.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased (Pam) and floured 9x13x2 pyrex baking dish.	Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Dust top with powdered sugar and cut into squares.
Serve warm plain or with vanilla ice-cream.	Also good the next day or so.
Serves 24.
(Bake a little longer if too soft in the center.)

title: frankie's grandma urestis' oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add sifted flour mixture, oats, raisins and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°. Cook until light brown.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows.
Stir until melted.
Crush crackers.
Mix with fruit and nuts.
Pour milk mixture in and mix well.
Pack well in dish.
Press with fingers.
Refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Hints:
Separate popped corn from seeds.
Don't overcook.
As it starts cooling, it will stick together.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes. Cut into thick slices and cook with onion. Drain water when potatoes are done. Mix with electric mixer and add 1/2 cup margarine, cream cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper. Place into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Dot with margarine. Refrigerate until ready to use. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until hot. Garnish with paprika.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, onion, carrot, celery and bouillon cubes in water to cover until chicken test tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients in pan with fork until moistened.
Beat vigorously for 1 minute.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a large mixing bowl. Stir in honey, shortening, salt, warm water and whole wheat flour. Mix until smooth.
Add enough all-purpose flour to make dough easy to handle.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers 5 minutes.
Sprinkle inside of peppers with salt.

title: barbara t's creamy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Pat firmly on bottom of buttered spring-form pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat orange juice to dissolve cherry jello.
While hot, dissolve the unflavored gelatin (which has been softened in 2 tablespoons water).
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into salad mold or 8-inch square dish and refrigerate.

title: baked sauerkraut wirth
directions: Spread sauerkraut in buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Cover with the tomatoes and juice and sprinkle the brown sugar on top.
Arrange the bacon on top and bake at 300° for 2 hours. Remove from oven and cut bacon in pieces and stir back into mixture.
Bake 1 hour.
Add water so mixture does not dry out. Serves 8.

title: hush puppies ii
directions: Combine ingredients, except buttermilk and oil, adding enough buttermilk to make a stiff batter.
Drop by spoonful into hot oil to brown.
Delicious with fried fish.

title: pecan crisp cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugar and oleo.
Add well beaten eggs and mix.
Add dry ingredients and pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: yogurt pudding("quick and easy dessert!")
directions: Stir instant pudding with milk.
Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix pudding and fruit together.
Add yogurt and whipped topping.
Add food coloring and marshmallows, if desired.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the margarine, peanut butter and sugar in bowl.
Add Rice Krispies and shape into balls.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Roll balls in chocolate and pull out with tongs.
Cool on wax paper.
(Great for parties!)

title: pineapple-orange salad
directions: Measure out 2 cups of fruit juice (1 cup of each).
Add to pudding; bring to a boil.
Add fruit and chill.
Add raisins or bananas, if desired.

title: chicken planks
directions: Mix flour, egg, paprika, salt and pepper in a bowl. Add milk until thin. Dip chicken in mixture. Pan or deep-fry.

title: lime pie
directions: Beat 2 tablespoons sugar and egg yolks together.
Beat the condensed milk into egg mixture.
Add lime juice and food coloring and stir.
Pour into prebaked pie shell.
Whip egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar together, adding the sugar gradually.
Spread over the pie and place in 350° oven to brown the top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Precook spinach and drain well.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Chill.
Roll into 1 inch balls and freeze on cookie sheet.
Place in plastic bags when thoroughly frozen.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Spread over cake mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet soup or fruit soup
directions: Cook the raisins and prunes in the water until done.
Add the fruit juice.
Boil 1 minute.
Add the tapioca or rice and cook until clear or done.
Remove from heat and add the sugar and sliced lemon.
Serve when cold.

title: favorite fruit punch
directions: Pour liquid in	large
container, add sugar as desired, stir and chill.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Using Martha White self-rising meal, follow directions on the package for corn bread, adding 6 eggs.
Bake.
When bread is done, crumble and add other ingredients.
Stir.
Add chicken broth and leave the mixture lumpy.
Add chicken, if desired.
Cook in 3-quart casserole dish until vegetables are done and brown on top.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; peel and slice. Mix with half of the onion and parsley. Fry half of onion in bacon fat. Add flour and stir until smooth. Add sugar, vinegar and water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Mix while adding potatoes; season with salt and pepper.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
in large pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat, beat until cool and add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper to harden.

title: banana cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled squash
directions: Sprinkle salt over squash and onions. Let stand 1 hr.
Combine remaining ingreds. in large saucepan and bring to boil. When boiling pour over squash and onions. Return mixture to pan and bring to a boil. Pack in jars and seal.
Yield 4 pints.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut the spareribs into serving pieces and place in a baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the spareribs. Cover.
Bake at 350° until meat of spareribs is tender, turning once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ninth street house tea
directions: Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat until bubbly.
Put in ovensafe dish and top with Bisquick biscuits.
Bake according to directions on Bisquick box for biscuits (450° for 10 minutes).

title: peanut butter round-up cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and peanut butter; beat well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fork tines.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli in 1/2 cup of water.
Add the butter and the onion.
Cook until onion is done.
Mix in the Cheez Whiz and the undiluted mushroom soup, then the raw rice.
Mix well and put into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: easy upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup syrup.
Melt margarine in ovenproof pan (such as an iron skillet).
Blend in the brown sugar.
Remove
from heat.
Arrange pineapple in mixture.
Place a cherry in the middle of each pineapple hole.
Prepare cake according to directions, replacing milk with pineapple syrup. Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
All measurements are approximate and should be to taste but there should be more brown sugar than catsup.
Pour in large baking pan and top with bacon strips.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
May place in crock-pot for easier transportation.

title: cantaloupe ice cream pie
directions: Blend crackers until fine crumbs form.
Melt margarine and combine with crackers until crumbs form ball.
Press mixture into 9-inch pie plate.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Place cantaloupe in blender and blend for 30 seconds.
Swirl mixture through ice cream.
Firmly pack ice cream into crust.
Cover.
Freeze several hours or until firm.

title: broccoli casserole ii
directions: Cook broccoli according to the directions; pour off excess water; set aside.
In the top of double boiler, melt cheese with mushroom soup while onions and celery are being sauteed in margarine.
Combine these two mixtures along with mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Into a large greased casserole dish, pour broccoli; then the above mixture and top with Ritz crackers.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, oleo and corn syrup in medium size saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Pour over Krispies.
Mix well.
Pour in greased square pan.
Cool and cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: In a large pan, combine chicken, water, onion slices, celery, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Strain broth, discarding vegetables; return broth to pan.
Add tomatoes, carrots, onion and bouillon cubes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until the carrots are tender.
When chicken is cool enough to handle, remove bones and skin.
Cube chicken and add to broth along with zucchini.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Just before serving, garnish with avocado slices.
This is a wonderfully fresh soup and very hearty, too!

title: pea & corn salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables together in a very large bowl.
You'll need stirring room.
Mix dressing, vinegar, sugar and water together.
Pour over vegetables and stir well.
Refrigerate and serve the next day.
Best made a day ahead so all the flavors mingle.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix fruit, pudding and coconut.
Add Cool Whip, then marshmallows.
Chill overnight.

title: beans and greens
directions: Cook ham bits in 1 to 2 cups water until falling apart (10 minutes).
While the ham is cooking in the bottom of a good size pot, wash the kale.
Remove curly, leafy parts of kale from stems and wash.
Add to pot with cooking ham pieces and cook until kale is soft.
Add the 2 cans of beans and cook, covered, until the beans are soft (some begin to break apart).

title: dangerous dan's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all ingredients into large pot and heat on low for 20 minutes.

title: corn and chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat a 9 x 13 baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken halves in single layer in baking dish. Sprinkle with seasonings.
In large bowl, combine stuffing mix, corn, water and butter.
Mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
In same bowl, combine soup, milk and parsley.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes or until stuffing is golden brown.

title: shrimp butter spread
directions: Chop shrimp fine in blender.
Melt cheese and butter in microwave until it blends smoothly.
Add shrimp, garlic, onion and Accent.
Whisk until well blended.
Pour into shallow dish and chill.
Serve at room temperature on crackers or veggies.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine fat, flour, milk and salt; cook until thickened. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and sauce in greased casserole dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham and lima beans
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot and stir together well. Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 hours.
Very good with cornbread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and water; set aside.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter; set aside 1 cup.
Press remaining cracker crumbs on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook chicken with bouillon cube. Add cut up, cooked chicken to soup mixture.
Spread over crumbs in baking dish.
Add remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop lettuce, onion, bell peppers and tomatoes.
Add lettuce, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes, ground beef, kidney beans and cheese in a large container.
Right before serving, add Doritos and pour over Good Seasons Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Serve.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate; remove from heat and add sugar and eggs.
Beat well and add flour, salt and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute pepper and mushrooms.
Add flour and cook until thick. Add chicken and sour cream.
Cook until butter comes to the top. Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: apricot lassi
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
You can substitute 1/2 c. pineapple juice for nectar.

title: lemon cups
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt. Add to melted butter. Add lemon juice and lemon rind. Mix well. Add egg yolks and milk; stir well. Fold in egg whites. Pour into buttered custard cups. Place in pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until lightly brown on top. Remove from pan. Cool and refrigerate.

title: sausage and bean casserole
directions: Fry sausage patties until done, then place on paper towel to drain excess grease.
Mix pinto beans and tomatoes (drain about 1/3 of juice from tomatoes before mixing), onion and green pepper. Spray 9 x 9-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in bean mixture. Place sausage patties on top and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix
softened
cream
cheese, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add vanilla,
then
add
cake mix.
Fold in (drained) blueberries. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Remove cake immediately.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into rapidly boiling milk.
Cook until very thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
The mixture will be cold and very stiff.
Add well beaten eggs, salt, baking powder and melted butter.
Beat with electric beater 15 minutes.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve from casserole by spoonfuls.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Can add more onion and seasoned salt to taste.

title: no fuss baked noodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles, drain and return to pan. Add all other ingredients and mix gently.
Transfer mixture to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Blend softened butter, cream cheese and unthawed Cool Whip with a mixer.
Add milk and dry pudding.
