Beat until smooth. Place in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour until thickened. Crush cookies in blender.
Layer cookies, then pudding mixture, ending with cookies.
"Gummy worms" can be placed on top for effect, if desired.

title: wet cake
directions: Stir together and bake at 325° in greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes.
Cool cake for 10 minutes and add icing.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Mix all together (do not drain pineapple).
Pour into baking dish; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Work in shortening until it resembles corn meal.
Add milk until dough is hard to handle and moist.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Place dough on floured wax paper; sprinkle top with flour and pat to about 2-inch thickness.
Cut with glass or biscuit cutter and place on pan with each biscuit touching.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until done and top is slightly brown.

title: pickle beans
directions: Bring beans to a boil and cook 1/2 hour.
Drain off hot water and rinse in cold water.
Cool beans and press firmly into jars. Make brine of salt and 1/2 gallon water and pour over beans. Tighten lids after 10 days.

title: bobbi lou's apple dumplings
directions: Wrap the apples in the crescent rolls and place in a baking dish.
Mix sugar, butter and water.
Make sure the butter and sugar are melted and dissolved.
Pour mixture over crescent rolls. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: creamy cheesecake
directions: Have cream
cheese
at room temperature.
Mix well with sugar. Add sour
cream
and
mix.	Add
vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into
graham
cracker crust and let chill 4 hours. Use your choice of topping.	Makes 2 pies.

title: banana bran nut bread
directions: Combine egg, bananas, shortening and bran. Sift dry ingredients and add nuts; then add to first mixture. Mix only enough to dampen flour. Bake in greased pan at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: chocolate bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add egg; mix until well blended.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture.
Press remainder of crumbs in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, combine condensed milk and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Over low heat, cook and stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Spread evenly over crust.
Add nuts and remaining 1 cup chocolate chips to reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: sour cream blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
If using food processor, put metal blade in.
Add sugar, egg, sour cream and oil.
Pulse on and off for 5 seconds or until thoroughly blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to processor.
Pulse on and off once or twice until just blended.
Stir in berries and scrape down sides.
Mix.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: deer steaks
directions: Let frozen steaks thaw in water.
Rinse and soak in water for about 2 hours.
Rinse and examine steaks, cutting off any white elastic like grissle.
Cover with about 3 tablespoons salt and water.
Soak for about 2 more hours.
Rinse and soak in water 1 hour longer (or overnight).
Place in crock-pot with soup, salt, pepper, oil and water to make pot at least 2/3 full.
Mix well and let cook on high for about 4 hours or on low about 5 1/2 hours. The longer you soak the meat the better and the slower you cook the meat the better.
May also add chopped onions.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump crushed pineapple into pan and spread evenly.
Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Dump box of yellow cake mix dry (add nothing).
Sprinkle chopped pecans over cake mix.
Slice butter into pan on top of cake.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Use 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in chunks.
Cover potatoes in water.
Boil until done.
Drain potatoes.
Leave 2 or 3 tablespoons of water and then add chopped eggs, pimento and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk together and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Stir well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, (will be thick).

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Brown small amount of chopped onion in butter.
Pour uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish. Place browned chicken on top and pour chicken soup on top.
Add water.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: idiot's delight
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, chocolate bits, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts with butter.
Pour condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into squares after allowing it to cool.
Very rich candy.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Whip eggs; mix together sugar and flour.
Then add milk, coconut and butter.
Add 2 tablespoons vanilla if desired.
If no crust is used, grease 6 to 7 pie plates well.
Pour mix into crusts or plates.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes. Monitor temperature so crust will not brown before filling begins to set and brown.
Yields 8 pies in crust or 6 to 7 without crust.

title: apricot and pineapple jam
directions: Combine
apricots and pineapple.
Heat adding Sure-Jell and sugar.
Cook slowly until thick. Makes about 7 1/2 pints.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead 1 to 2 minutes and shape into rounded loaf.
Brush top with milk.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli.
Cut into pieces and florets.
Place in casserole dish. Add 2 tablespoons water. Cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High for 6 minutes. Drain off water.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Cheddar cheese.
Pour over broccoli. Spread evenly. Crush Better Cheddar crackers and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chops sauterne
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown chops slowly; drain off excess grease.
Spread each chop with mustard, then with brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Top chops with lemon slices.
Pour Sauterne over meat.
Cover and cook slowly until tender, 50 to 60 minutes. Remove meat to hot plate and pour sauce over meat.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine undrained corn, muffin mix, 1/4 stick of margarine, sour cream, eggs and cheese, except for 1/3 cup reserved for topping.
Mix.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean and meat bake
directions: Cut luncheon meat into 8 slices. Brush each slice with syrup, reserving remaining syrup.
Arrange meat slices around edge of a 9-inch pie plate.
In saucepan, combine beans, remaining syrup, onion, flour and mustard.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Pour boiling bean mixture into pie plate. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until meat is lightly browned, about 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chardonnay chicken
directions: Lightly flour chicken and fry in 4 tablespoons butter until golden brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Place in warm oven. Add the other 4 tablespoons butter to pan.
Saute onions and garlic in butter; add wine and lemon juice.
Simmer on low for 5 minutes.
Add chicken to sauce; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Beat in sugar gradually until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extracts. Gradually beat in combined flour and salt until well blended. Spread in buttered and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Cut through butter with knife.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Invert onto rack and cool completely.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Add water as needed during cooking.
Use glass casserole dish to bake or cook in crock-pot.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, ham and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. In saucepan, combine soups, onion and one can of water.
Mix well. Pour over potatoes, ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender, about 45 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients and shape into balls. Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over meatballs. Bake for 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Beat well. Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.
Drizzle with glaze of 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons hot water.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, place the potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix the ground beef with the evaporated milk, oats, chili sauce, onion, salt and pepper and spread over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: festive fudge blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350 cut butter into cake mix in large bowl until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg and water until well blended.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain and pat dry as possible. Combine with remaining ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate several hours.

title: iowa corn chowder
directions: In Dutch oven, over medium heat, cook bacon till crisp.
Pour off all but 2 Tbsp. of drippings, remove bacon.
Add chicken, onion, and celery.
Cook 10-15 minutes or till tender, stirring. In blender combine 1 c. chicken broth and 2 c. corn.
Blend till smooth.
In Dutch oven, stir in pureed corn mixture and remaining 2 c. of corn, potatoes, remaining broth, and salt.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in cream, parsley and pepper.
Simmer 2-3 minutes.
Taste and season.
Stir in bacon.
Serve.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Allow butter and cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients to form a stiff dough.
Form small ball or use cookie press. Flatten to make wafer shape. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: whiskey or bourbon balls(make these a week ahead)
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
form
into
small balls.
If balls tend to
crumble,
add a few drops of liquor to mixture. Roll each in powdered sugar and store in an airtight container for about
1 week to ripen.
Yield:
4 dozen (1/2-inch) balls. Calories per serving:

title: oriental salad
directions: Optional: Chinese pea pods, frozen green peas, cubed chicken, sliced water chestnuts, etc.

title: pudding cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions, using 2 round layer pans.
Cool and remove from pans, putting each layer on separate plates.
Cover tightly (each plate) with aluminum foil.
Set aside.

title: tasty green beans
directions: Fry fat back.
Remove meat and add beans, tomatoes, onions and sugar.
Cook until done and then salt and pepper.

title: quick cornlight bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool and slice.
Fry each slice in butter until brown.

title: chocolate chip wheat germ squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease glass baking dish and line with wax paper.
Grease top part of wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and then remove wax paper.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let set.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix flour, cinnamon and soda together.
Add alternately with oatmeal mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, bread crumbs, salt and pepper to taste. Form into meatballs.
Cook in skillet on low to medium heat until done.
Drain any grease. Add butter, onion and green pepper and cook another 2 to 3 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine the soups and sour cream together and mix.
Turn heat down on low and add the soup mixture.
Let simmer on low for 20 minutes. Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk, sour cream and Cool Whip.
In 3-quart casserole dish, place layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.

title: braised cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers once lengthwise and once crosswise.
Sprinkle with pepper and saute lightly in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water and add to pan.
Cook covered over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together everything but only 1/3 cup margarine and not the cornflakes.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish. Mix remaining 1/3 cup margarine with the cornflakes. Sprinkle over the potatoes. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: brownie cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and soda and set aside.
Put water, oil, butter and cocoa in pot and bring to boil.
Pour this over dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Bake in greased pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Soften
yeast in lukewarm water, about 5 minutes.
Pour milk over sugar and salt in a bowl.
Stir until dissolved and slightly cooled.
Add 1 cup flour, beat until smooth.
Beat in shortening, eggs, softened yeast and remaining flour.
Mix to a soft dough. Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Knead for 5
to
minutes or
until
dough becomes smooth.
Place in lightly
greased bowl,
greasing
top
of
dough.
Cover with greased
wax
paper and
allow
to rise in a warm place until double.
Roll out to 1/3-inch thickness and cut with a floured doughnut
cutter.
Let rise
on
the
board until very light. Drop into
hot
fat
and turn as soon as they rise to the surface.
Drain
on
absorbent paper.
While
warm, glaze with a mixture of 1/3 cup boiling water and 1 cup confectioners sugar or dust with granulated or confectioners sugar.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in the microwave.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
When completely blended, press into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill and cut into pieces.

title: chicken-sausage casserole
directions: Let chicken cook in boiling water for only 2 to 3 minutes to aid in boning, then remove.
To 3 cups chicken stock, add soup mix and rice.
Boil 9 minutes.
Watch this mixture to see that it does not stick or dry out!
Crumble and fry sausage and add to soup-rice mixture.
Chop vegetables and brown in sausage drippings.
Add to mixture with remaining ingredients including boned and chunked chicken.
Mix well and put in casserole lightly treated with nonstick cooking spray.
Serves 6 but great for doubling and for freezing.
Thaw if necessary, then bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: manwich night meat loaf
directions: Mix the ground beef, crumbs, onion, salt, egg and pepper with 1/2 cup sauce.
Shape into loaf and place in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Drain.
Spread mustard over loaf and pour remaining sauce over it.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit 'n' nut snack cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Sift or stir together flour and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: cherro treats
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter jelly roll pan.
Heat first 4 items in 4-quart saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Take off heat and stir in Cheerios and nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Run spatula under mix and break up.
Let cool for about an hour.
Put in Tupperware.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Combine flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook slowly until thick, stirring constantly.
Beat, in mixer, butter and vegetable shortening until smooth.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until all is the texture of whipped cream.

title: peppers
directions: Cut peppers in eighths.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 400° until cooked.
Use on sandwiches.
Put in jar and store in refrigerator.

title: yogurt cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumber and red onion slices in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over slices; toss.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings (1/2 cup each); 36 calories per serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese.
Soften butter.
Put all ingredients in mixer and mix thoroughly.
Put through cookie press.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes about 100 cheese straws.

title: cheese chili dip
directions: Grate cheese. Put cream of mushroom soup in pot (undiluted). Put cheese into cream of mushroom soup and heat on low.
Add the chilies and stir. Do not boil.
Mixture will be thick when done.

title: pink or purple passion
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in serving bowl.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in tepid water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Combine flour, 4 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in butter.
Add buttermilk,
then yeast mixture to flour.
Mix thoroughly and knead a few minutes on a floured board.
Cut into biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and cover while oven heats to 400°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Blend dry ingredients and cut in mayo with fork.
Add water and knead until smooth.
Cover and let stand for fifteen minutes. Form balls and roll each one flat, trying to keep a round shape (not easy, takes practice).
Fry one at a time in a hot dry skillet or on a tortilla griddle.
Resist the temptation to grease the cooking surface!
When large bubbles form, they can be flattened with a spatula.
Good eating!

title: stuffed peppers and tomatoes
directions: Chop parsley and onion and scoop out tomatoes and chop some of the insides of it and add some gravy left over from a roast or use BV gravy.
Add the hamburger and washed rice and have pepper seeds scooped out.
Salt the insides of the tomatoes and peppers and fill in with the meat mixture, put tops of peppers and tomatoes back on it.
Put in baking pan in oven with boiling water or beef stock and some tomato juice.
Cover over with another pan and bake until tender.
Baste the tops of the peppers and tomatoes once in awhile so the rice will be cooked on the top.
Usually takes 1 hour or more.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet with shortening.
Remove chops from skillet and brown onion slightly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place chops in baking dish; pour sauce over chops and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: charcoal broiled fish fillet
directions: Place perforated foil on medium hot grill and place fish on one half of it.
To turn, fold other half of foil over and turn quickly with large spatula.
Sprinkle top side of fillet with dill weed and garlic powder.
Cook about 5 minutes and turn.
After 5 minutes more, sprinkle other side with lemon pepper and paprika. Serve with tartar sauce and seasoned brown rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt together 1/3 stick oleo, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: pineapple casserole #2
directions: Drain pineapple and put in large casserole dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over pineapple.
Melt 1 stick of margarine. Crush plain Ritz crackers (or Cheese Nips) to make 1 cup of crumbs.
Mix crumbs with margarine and pour on top of mixture. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole, except cheese.
Cover; cook at least 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Check pot.
If soft, remove cover. Put on cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Combine dry ingredients.
Mix both together.
Divide into two balls.
Chill at least one hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package.
Mix juice according to can.
Add drink.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: jon spaghetti
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and bell pepper; drain.
Use separate saucepan and combine tomato sauce, water, mushrooms, pepper, oregano and cumin.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix spaghetti with meat mixture and sauce.
Cut cheese into cubes and put on top of spaghetti.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: english muffin bread(must be toasted)
directions: Lightly grease 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans. Coat each with 1 tablespoon cornmeal.
Mix 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda in a large bowl.
Heat milk and water in a saucepan until warm (105° to 115°).
Stir into flour mixture. Stir in remaining flour.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Sprinkle tops with remaining cornmeal.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Heat chocolate bars, marshmallows and milk in a double boiler until chocolate and marshmallows are melted.
Cool thoroughly.

title: sour cream yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine sour cream, sugar and soda in large bowl; mix well.
Add 2 cups baking mix and yeast; mix until well blended.
Stir in 3 cups baking mix until soft dough forms.
Knead on surface dusted with remaining 1/4 cup baking mix until smooth and elastic.
Shape into walnut sized rolls.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown. Yield: 72 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make crust with dry ingredients and milk.
Roll out.
Cut in 6 squares.
Put apples on dough; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 360° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and top with whipped cream.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Place frozen broccoli in greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour corn over broccoli.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over corn. Drizzle margarine over stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until broccoli is tender.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Beat juices into marshmallow cream.
Beat in mayonnaise. Great dip for any kind of fruit.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Sprinkle nuts on top before baking.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
This keeps well in freezer.

title: light brown sugar brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar and continue beating until well blended.
Add flour and mix.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: mary grilc's cheese strukle
directions: On a towel, lay 6 sheets of phyllo dough.
Melt butter and brush all over, but not on each sheet.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake
as
directed on box.
Bake in 2 Pyrex dishes. Mix jello
as directed and pour over cake when cool.
Mix Cool Whip and strawberries together and spread over cake.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add vanilla, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Gradually add flour, coconut and pecans.
Beat the egg whites and fold in last. Pour into 3 round baking pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° until tests done.
Cool.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle into pan in this order:
graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, chopped pecans, coconut and milk.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together apples, sugar and cinnamon in a 9-inch round or square pan.
Mix flour and butter until crumbly; place on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: homemade reeses cups
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, confectioners sugar and melted butter.
Mix thoroughly and roll out into patties.
Melt paraffin with chocolate. Put 1 teaspoon chocolate in the bottom of a cupcake paper or custard cup.
Put in 1 patty and add another teaspoon of chocolate to cover patty.
Continue this process until all patties have been covered with chocolate. Keeps well in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: dream dessert
directions: Mix butter, nuts and flour.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: swiss mocha mix
directions: Mix thoroughly.
For 1 cup of beverage, use 3 tablespoons to 3/4 cup of boiling water.

title: easy yum yum
directions: Bottom layer:
Spread sugar cookie dough in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake until golden brown.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Press meat into 9 x 12-inch (or similar) casserole dish. Sprinkle with soup mix.
Spread with cream of mushroom soup. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot; freeze leftovers.

title: oriental turkey stir-fry
directions: Cut turkey into 1/2 x 1-inch strips.
Combine soy sauce, sherry and garlic.
Stir in turkey and let stand 15 minutes.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large nonstick skillet or wok until hot. Stir-fry turkey in oil until no longer pink.
Remove turkey from skillet.
Add additional tablespoon of oil if desired.
Add broccoli and red pepper; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and pea pods.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add green onions and bean sprouts; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Combine chicken broth and cornstarch.
Add this mixture to the vegetables.
Stir in turkey.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir until sauce is thickened and clear.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately over rice. Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to fill a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Season as you would for apple pie, only use 1/2 as much sugar. Butter baking dish and add apples.

title: sparkling citrus punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl. Serve over ice. Makes 30 servings (about 2/3 cup each).

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cream together brown sugar & butter. Add in flour and pecans. Press mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes. Let cool completely. Cream together cream cheese & sugar. Add Cool Whip. Spread over crust. Top with sliced strawberries or choice of fruit.

title: egg nog
directions: In blender mix eggs and sugar for 10 to 15 seconds.
Add rum, whiskey or vanilla.
Add cream; mix together for 5 seconds.
Add cinnamon or nutmeg and mix for 5 seconds.
Mix again before serving.

title: spiced baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice, not all the way through, slightly separate potatoes.
Melt magarine.
Add seasonings.
Pour over potatoes in a microwave dish.
Cover with waxed paper or Saran Wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Spoon seasoned butter over top when serving.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, two at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring. Add sifted dry ingredients (reserving 1/2 cup flour to dredge raisins).
Add coconut, apples and raisins. Bake in greased paper lined tube cake pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: filled eggplant
directions: Mix ingredients except eggplant.
Slice eggplant about 1/2-inch thick.
Take this slice and slit like pocket.
Fill with ball of filling.
Place oil in frypan.
Just brown eggplant.
Salt and pepper each side to taste.
Line bottom of roaster pan with one layer of filled eggplant.
In saucepan, cook fresh tomato, parsley and basil (no oil).
Pour 1/2 mixture over eggplant. Place other slices on top of first layer; pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix the flour with baking soda.
Combine the margarine, sugar, pudding mix and vanilla.
In a large bowl, beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts to chocolate mixture.
Shape into 2-inch rolls.
Roll in coconut.
Slice in 1/2-inch slices.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ranchero macaroni bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine soup and milk.
Stir in macaroni, cheese and salsa.
Spoon into a 3-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle chips over macaroni mixture.
Bake 5 minutes more or until hot and bubbling.

title: homer's famous meat loaf
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients except catsup and tomato sauce.
Shape loaf in large roaster.
Spread 1/2 can tomato sauce and catsup on loaf and around loaf in roaster.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and baste again with catsup and the other 1/2 can of tomato sauce. Precooked carrots may be placed around the meat loaf in the sauce. Bake 45 minutes more or until done.

title: best all-around punch
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add lemonade, almond extract and juice.
May freeze part of this in a ring or in plastic milk jugs to be used to chill the punch in a punch bowl or to save in the freezer for later use.
Add 7-Up when serving.

title: milwaukee pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both
sides;
mix
brown sugar, beer and ketchup together and pour
over
browned
chops.
Let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
If drying, add a little more beer or water.

title: breakfast potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread potatoes in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Top with onion, bell pepper, bacon, corn and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings with 350 calories per serving.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift all dry ingredients 3 times.
Add to sugar and shortening, alternating with tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: yankee chicken 'n rice
directions: Oil a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: rice and hamburger dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butter semmeln (rolls)
directions: This batter must be made in the early evening and set to rise in a warm place until morning.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix and drop from teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white sangria
directions: In a punch bowl put the
orange, lemon and lime slices. Cover with sugar and press the fruit so that juice runs.	Stir until sugar is dissolved and add raspberries or strawberries.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 2-quart baking dish. Mix undiluted soup, milk and sherry in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredient, except cheese.
Toss gently to mix.
Turn into prepared dish.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 servings, 378 calories per serving.

title: sauce for beets
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in vinegar and water.
Add sugar and salt. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat in 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour over beets.

title: not your ordinary hamburger
directions: Combine all ingredients with ground beef.
Make into patties. Fry in skillet in just enough olive oil to cover bottom.

title: overnight green salad
directions: Put ingredients in large bowl (a clear bowl looks very pretty) in order as listed.

title: chinese pepper steaks
directions: Cut steaks into thin strips.
Brown steaks and onion in hot oil.
Add
black pepper.
Drain oil.
Add water and bouillon. Cover
and reduce heat.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Add green pepper and simmer 5
to
minutes.
Blend cornstarch with a little water.
Add to broth and stir until slightly thickened. Add soy sauce.
Serve hot over rice or egg noodles.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add milk and egg to spaghetti and place in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Brown and drain hamburger.
Add garlic salt.
Pour over spaghetti mixture.
Spread chopped onion over hamburger, then mushrooms over onions. Spread spaghetti sauce over all and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning or when ready to serve bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: holiday yams with marshmallows
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add yams just until desired texture is reached.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cover half of time.
Let marshmallows brown slightly.

title: easy chicken fricassee and herb dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients with a fork.
Spoon over boiling stew.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken breasts wrapped in chipped beef
directions: Parboil chicken gently until tender.
Strip chicken of all skin, bone and tendons.
Wrap each breast in thin slice of chipped beef.
Place in baking dish.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Can be served with hollowed out dark rye bread or crackers or regular party rye bread.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press roll dough into 11 x 15-inch baking pan or large pizza pan, sealing perforations.
Bake using crescent roll can directions.
Cool to room temperature.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Save 2/3 cup for top.
Melt butter.
Add crushed cookies.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Fold in 1/2 Cool Whip. Spread on cookie mixture and refrigerate it again.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Add rest of Cool Whip over pudding.
Then add remaining 2/3 cup cookie crumbs.

title: 3 bean chili
directions: In large saucepan, combine gravy, tomatoes and chili powder; bring to a boil.
Stir in beans and chilies.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with desired toppings.

title: sawmill gravy
directions: Cook sausage until brown in a large skillet over medium heat. Drain and reserve 2 tablespoons of the drippings in skillet. Blend in flour; brown, stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce flame.
Add sausage, salt and pepper; cook, stirring constantly, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy kettle.
Cut onion and celery in chunks; chop finely in food processor.
Saute onion and celery until clear. Add flour.
Stir and cook over low heat 3 minutes.
Add pumpkin puree.
Mix thoroughly while heating 5 minutes.
Return to food processor.
Process until smooth.
Return to kettle; add stock. Heat to boiling, then simmer.
Five minutes before serving add milk and spices.
Continue heating but do not boil.
Serve with croutons.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Set aside cooked chicken.
Saute together onions, margarine and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, chilies, sugar, cumin, salt, oregano and basil.
Simmer approximately 15 minutes.

title: shrimp or crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute butter, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Add crawfish (or shrimp), garlic, parsley and green onions.
Cook for 20 minutes. Add pepper cheese and half and half.
Put in Corning Ware dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325 for 20 minutes.
Boil noodles and have ready to add to cooked ingredients.
Mix well and serve.

title: layered dip
directions: Combine sour cream, salt and dill weed in a bowl.
Mix well. On a 12 to 16-inch serving platter, spread sour cream mixture to 1/4-inch thickness.

Sprinkle evenly with cheese. Spread onion dip over cheese. Top with onions, olives and egg. Garnish with paprika and parsley. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours before serving. Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Makes 6 cups.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and molasses.
Mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk to batter and mix well.
Bake in layers 1/2-inch thick, in 9-inch pans for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Put into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Drain beans and put on top.
Next, arrange Tater Tots on beans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Mix soup with milk and pour over casserole.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and toss with crumbled corn bread.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In medium pot over medium heat, combine water and sugar and dissolve. Add peanuts and continue cooking. Stir frequently until peanuts are completely sugar coated and the sugar is crystallized and there is no syrup left. Pour mixture onto an ungreased cookie sheet, spreading and separating the peanuts as much as possible. Bake until nuts are golden, about 12 to 15 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals.

title: chocolate nut bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Melt the chocolate and butter in a small pan over low heat; set aside to cool.
Stir and toss together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Place the sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and nuts in a large mixing bowl and beat them together until blended.
Add the combined dry ingredients and the chocolate mixture and beat just until the batter is smooth.
Divide the batter evenly between the prepared pans and bake for about 45 minutes, or until a broom straw inserted in the center of a loaf comes out clean.
Remove from the oven and let cool in the pans for about 5 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.

title: yam casserole delight
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ranch roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a gallon size storage bag and add oil; seal bag and toss to coat.
Add seasoning and toss again until coated. Bake in ungreased baking pan at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are brown and crisp.

title: chocolate macaroon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Cool and put 2 cookies together, filling with vanilla frosting.

title: prune bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.
Make a nest.
Add oil, eggs, prunes and sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour tube pan or 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato skin appetizer
directions: Scrub potatoes; rub with oil.
Prick potatoes with fork and bake at 375° for 1 hour until tender.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes into halves lengthwise.
Scoop out interiors.
With scissors, cut skins lengthwise into strips.
Brush insides of skins with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Place on ovenproof platter.
Preheat broiler.
Slip skins under heat until cheese melts.

title: microwave karmelcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, Karo and salt in a microwave-safe container.
On High, boil ingredients for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Put popcorn in large, heavy brown paper bag (grocery type).
Pour caramel sauce over the popcorn and shake the bag vigorously.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Remove bag and shake well.
Microwave for another 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Spread popcorn on waxed paper to cool.

title: zurish potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and grate them into cold water.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain and squeeze all liquid out by handfuls.
Dry on clean toweling.
Melt half the butter in a large skillet; add grated onion and pepper and saute for two minutes.
Add the drained potatoes.
Sprinkle thickly with paprika; cover tightly and cook over very low heat for 15 minutes.
Check occasionally to be sure the potatoes are not sticking to the bottom of the pan, but do not stir or disarrange.
Add extra butter, if needed, by lifting potatoes carefully with a spatula.
Carefully slide potatoes onto a warm plate.
Melt remaining butter in skillet and invert potatoes in skillet.
Continue to cook another 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter, cream cheese and whipped topping in a large bowl; mix well. Spoon into pie shell. Chill until serving time.

title: texas skillet cobbler
directions: Melt oleo.
Place fruit in oblong pan.
Sweeten, if desired. Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour melted oleo over fruit.
Pour sugar and flour mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven after heat is turned off to allow topping to get crusty.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Pour over Peanut Butter Fingers, baked.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder three times.
Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beating well.
Add extracts.
Divide evenly into three greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 325° (preheat oven) for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on cake rack.

title: orange-kiss-me cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine 1/2 cup orange juice with remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Beat lowest speed for 30 seconds.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Drizzle remaining juice over warm cake and sprinkle with topping.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts well.
Mix in Parmesan cheese and mayonnaise.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top.
Serve with Wheat Thin crackers.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and cream cheese. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add flour; beat just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: don's fried fish
directions: Wash fillets thoroughly.
Shake together in paper bag the flour, corn meal and seasoning.
Dip fish, one piece at a time, in Pet milk.
Next drop in bag with dry ingredients and then fry in deep hot cooking oil (375°) until golden brown.

title: sweet and sour cabbage salad
directions: Put cabbage in large bowl.
Break dry noodles over cabbage. Sprinkle almonds and sesame seed over noodles and cabbage.
Add purple cabbage for color.
Bring to a boil the pepper, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Remove from heat and stir the Oriental flavor packet from noodles into dressing.
Stir well.
Pour over cabbage.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 cup ketchup.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar on top (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: great dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with milk.
Add dried beef, green bell pepper, dried onion flakes, garlic salt and pepper.
Fold into sour cream.
Place in serving dish.
Brown pecans in butter and salt.
Place on top.
Heat dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Also good chilled (chilled without pecans and butter).

title: taco dip
directions: Combine beans and cheese dip in bowl; mix well.
Spread in an 8 x 12-inch glass serving dish.
Combine taco seasoning mix, sour cream and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over bean mixture. Top with shredded cheese.
Sprinkle with green onions and tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield:
96 servings.

title: focaccia (italian flat bread)
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Let cool.
Mix yeast and 1/4 cup water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in oil, 1 cup water, mashed potatoes and salt.
Add 1 cup flour at a time, mixing well.
Knead on a floured surface until dough is velvety, smooth and a bit sticky.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise for 1 1/2 hours. Make sure bowl is covered.
Punch down and let rise again about 1 hour.
Oil a cookie sheet lightly and spread dough on sheet.
Put oil on hands to help spread dough.
Top dough with whatever you like (sauce, cheese, onions, peppers, etc.).
Bake bread for 5 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 400° and bake another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt together the chocolate and oleo; cool.
Beat eggs. Add sugar,
flour
and	vanilla.
Combine
mixtures
and beat again. Add
pecans.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan.	This makes its own crust.
Bake
at
for
30 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake. Center will be a little soft.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti and cook, then drain and cool.
Add eggs, milk, garlic powder, salt and half the shredded Mozzarella cheese. Mix together in a large bowl.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan or large baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Remove from oven.
Mix browned, drained hamburger with spaghetti sauce; spread on top of spaghetti crust.
Add pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares; serves 12 to 15.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix juice, vinegar, sugar, egg and flour; boil until thick. Cool.
When cool, add pineapple chunks, apples, marshmallows and peanuts.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Chill until served.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Arrange sauerkraut in bottom of a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.
Spoon dressing on top and add tomatoes and dot with butter.
Cube bread and toss in melted butter with caraway seeds.
Spread on top of other ingredients.
Bake in a preheated 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gooey turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package. Melt caramels in milk. Pour 1/2 of mixed cake mix into well greased and floured cake pan. Bake until firm. Remove and pour caramel mixture over baked cake and add chocolate chips over caramel mixture. Sprinkle chopped pecans over this (pecans optional). Pour rest of cake mix over and bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with milk chocolate frosting.

title: squash and peanut butter soup
directions: Thaw frozen squash.
In large heavy pot, bring broth to a boil.
Add squash.
Puree onion in processor.
(If using blender, add applesauce and a little of the broth mixture to puree onion.) Add onion and applesauce to broth mixture.
Reduce heat and cover pot.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 14-inch pan or 2 smaller pans.
Pour excess into a small bowl to be used later.
In medium bowl, mix apple pie filling with crushed pineapple.
Pour and spread out in buttered pans.
Over top sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts.
Pour reserved melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until golden and bubbly.
Serve warm or cool with whipped or ice cream, if desired.
Vary by using different fruits, cake mix or nuts.

title: indian fry bread for 100
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large dish pan. Fluff the dry ingredients with both hands.
This will make ingredients light and not be packed and heavy.
Make a well in the center.
Add liquid all at once.
Mix and work the dough with your hands until the dough gets elastic and stretchy.
Add enough flour until dough is easy to handle.
Let dough rest for 1 hour.
Pinch off a piece of dough and stretch and shape it into a circle about 1/4-inch thick.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on paper towels.

title: barbecue pork and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in salted water until tender. Cook rice until tender.
Mix broccoli, rice, Cheez Whiz and soup. Add chicken. Place
in 2-quart casserole. Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until bubbly or beginning to brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and soft butter with a pastry blender.
Crumble over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbling.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Put berries in bowl; add sugar mixed with flour or tapioca. Let stand until they draw liquid.
Add vinegar.
If they don't draw any juice, add 1/4 cup water.
If the berries have been frozen, they will be juicy.
Pour in pie shell, cut up butter and place over berries, then put on top crust.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until done.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with melted margarine. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Dissolve in 1 cup boiling water; set aside. Spread cream cheese/Cool Whip over pretzel crumbs in dish. Add slightly thawed strawberries to Jell-O.
Mix thoroughly and spread over cream cheese mixture in dish. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: bread salad
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Spread bread lightly with butter; cut into small cubes.
Add onion and eggs; refrigerate overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients in the morning and chill 3 to 4 hours. Garnish with cucumbers, tomatoes, etc.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1 tablespoon fat. Tear lettuce into bowl.
Add tomatoes, onion and seasonings. Combine vinegar and bacon fat; bring to a boil.
Toss with salad. Crumble bacon over salad.
This can be done in a chafing dish for service at the table.
Makes 6 servings.

title: luscious apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots and cover with water.
Simmer 10 minutes. Drain, cool and chop.
Combine butter, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup flour.
Mix until crumbly.
Press into greased 9-inch square pan, bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: linguine with spinach
directions: Break linguine into 1-inch lengths; set aside.
Saute carrot, celery and onion in butter in a Dutch oven until crisp-tender; add linguine and cook, stirring constantly, until pasta begins to brown.
Add water, bouillon cubes and garlic.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Place spinach on top of pasta; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Toss mixture.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp tempura
directions: Make dipping sauce by combining broth, sugar, soy sauce, sherry and ginger and/or radish.
Set aside.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter in olive oil.
Add all other ingredients except shrimp.
Let sauce stand for at least 15 minutes.
When ready to cook, add shrimp and sauce to skillet and cook for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Divide shrimp into individual bowls. Pour sauce over shrimp and serve with French bread for dipping. Messy but yum!
Finger bowls or hot hand towels will have your guests neat once more.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt together.
Beat eggs until lemony and add to mixture.
Blend well; add chopped nuts and vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into pie plate lined with uncooked pastry.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake until firm.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain well. Cover pie crust with cheese. Mix eggs, milk and pepper. Crumble sausage over cheese crust. Add milk-egg mixture. Cover mixture with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Test with knife. Don't overbake. Cool 5 minutes before serving. Makes 2 pies. Serve with fruit salad.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: carrot soup
directions: Heat slowly and add 2 pinches nutmeg, 1/2 teaspoon dried mint and dash of cinnamon.

title: **oatmeal icebox cookies
directions: Form roll, chill in refrigerator.
Slice thin and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice and saute onions in butter until soft.
Crush whole box of Cheez-Its and sprinkle on top of onions.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until Cheez-Its are brown on top.
Better if you use a glass baking dish.

title: corn 'n bacon chip dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; gradually blend in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries, oranges and apples through grinder.
Do not peel orange and only core apple.
Let stand 2 hours.

title: cheesy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done; mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, onions and seasonings.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with stuffing mix.
Spread 1/2 stuffing in bottom of pan.
Mix chicken, soup and broth together and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minute.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine crushed chips, garlic and black pepper. Salt chicken and dip in melted butter, then roll chicken in chips mixture. Place chicken, skin side up, in pan and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add to remaining ingredients. Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake dish 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with your favorite cream cheese icing.

title: lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and lemon rind.
Cream 1 cup sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time. Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in 3 of the 5 teaspoons of lemon juice.
Bake about 40 minutes.
After cooled, mix 2 teaspoons lemon juice and 2 tablespoons sugar and brush on loaves.

title: russian chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a nonstick casserole dish.
Mix together red Russian dressing, dry soup mix and apricot preserves. Pour mixture over chicken pieces.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low-fat hummus
directions: Puree beans with garlic in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients and adjust seasonings as needed.
Refrigerate and serve with sliced pita bread or raw vegetables.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute rice with butter until browned.
Place in baking dish and add bouillon, water, juice, mushrooms, almonds and green onions. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
May also cook in saucepan on stove top 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: secret pie crust
directions: Grease	well
three (1 pound) coffee cans and fill each 2/3 full.
Bake
hour
at
Let
cool	for 10 minutes before removing
from pan.
Bread may be stored several weeks in refrigerator
or freezer in washed and dried cans.	You may substitute	three
1/2-inch
bread pans for coffee cans, if desired, but
I
recommend using the coffee cans, they seem to turn out better.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix first five ingredients thoroughly until well blended. Roll out on floured board.
Cut in 1-inch rounds and place on ungreased pan.
Brush each round with egg white.
Place part of nut kernel on each.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: date nut tarts
directions: With electric mixer, beat the egg whites, Pet milk and water in a large bowl until stiff.
Beat in the sugar, a tablespoon at a time, to make a thick, glossy mixture.
Fold in all at once the soda cracker crumbs, nuts and dates.
Bake at 355° for 45 or 55 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine dry ingredients and pineapple in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring. Cool. Fold in cool whip, cottage cheese and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all together and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: southwest ~blt~ wrap
directions: Stir together salsa and corn.
Set aside.
Top 1 side of each tortilla evenly with bacon, lettuce, and corn salsa.
Drizzle with Avocado-Lime Sauce.
Roll up, and if desired, secure with wooded picks.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Cook beans as directed on package.
Set aside.
In large pan, place chopped onions, celery, peppers (bell and hot), mushrooms, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender in 3 or 4 cups water. Also, you may put in Molly McButter if you want it to have a buttery taste.
At this time add canned tomatoes, tomato paste and kidney beans.

title: broccoli-rice cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine all ingredients, except Cheez Whiz.
Place in baking dish.
Top with Cheez Whiz and microwave on High for 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter-chocolate cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake in oblong pan as directed.
Finish with Peanut Butter Broiled Icing.

title: doretha's casserole
directions: Heat shortening in frying pan; add diced potatoes, onion, pepper and water; cover pan and heat.
Stir mixture and cook until potatoes are nearly done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and eggs.
Alternate bananas and flour mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes and 35 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple in pan, spreading evenly.
In a separate bowl, mix blueberries and 3/4 cup sugar and blend.
Pour over crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over this mixture, leaving no berries in sight.
Melt oleo; pour over cake mix.
Mix together 1/4 cup sugar and chopped pecans and put them on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Halfway through the baking time, cut through cake with a knife to allow juice to come on top.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain
and
reserve juice from pineapple.
Mix together pineapple
and cheese in baking dish.
Combine sugar and flour with
juice and pour over pineapple-cheese mixture.
Melt oleo and mix
with
crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 3 minutes.
Add jello and juices. Stir.
Pour into milk cartons and freeze.
Use 3 liters ginger ale per run of punch.
Makes 44 punch cups per run.
Thaw 2 hours or longer before adding ginger ale to serve.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half and boil in water for 3 or 4 minutes. Scoop out pulp; leave 1/4-inch shell.
Set aside.
Finely chop the pulp.
Set aside.
In saucepan, cook onion in oil until tender. Add zucchini.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour, basil and pepper. Add milk, all at once.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Gradually add zucchini mixture to egg.
Stir in Parmesan.
Spoon mixture in zucchini shells.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until filling is browned.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add spices.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top, then sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture.
Slice butter and lay over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour together and add the lemon juice and rind, slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and salt.
Stir in the milk and mix well.
Beat the whites until stiff and fold into the first mixture.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 5 minutes.
Turn oven back to 350° and bake until the mixture will not adhere to the point of a knife inserted in the center or about 25 minutes longer.

title: dill buttered carrots
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 12 to 15 minutes or until carrots are done.
Serves 4.

title: banana muffins
directions: Beat egg slightly. Stir in remaining ingredients just until moistened. Divide batter evenly into 12 medium muffin cups that have been greased on the bottom.
Bake in a 400° preheated oven for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: scrambled pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger meat.
Add Chili-O mix.
Place cheese on top and let it melt.
Now, serve on hamburger buns or with saltines.
Serves 4 to 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken a l'orange
directions: Wash and dry chicken pieces and season with salt and pepper. Dredge with flour.
Heat shortening in a skillet.
Add chicken and brown lightly in oil on all sides.
Remove chicken to 3-quart casserole.
Drain fat from pan.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add other ingredients and beat well.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Bring to room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine pumpkin, milk, egg, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt. Pour into crust. Bake 15 minutes. Remove pie. Reduce oven temperature to 350°. Combine sugar, flour and remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Stir in walnuts. Sprinkle walnut mixture over pie and bake 40 minutes at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Makes 1 pie.

title: genoa hervey's tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in about 3 or 4 quarts of water until tender. Remove from broth and bone.
Add onion and green pepper to broth and cook a few minutes, or until tender.
Add noodles and cook about 10 minutes until they start to get tender.
Add mushroom soup.
Separately, scald 1 quart milk; do not stir much.
Add flour to 3/4 cup milk, then stir into hot milk to thicken.
Add oleo and cheese.
When cheese melts, add to noodle mixture, then boned chicken.
Put in casserole dishes or other container and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until mixture begins to brown or bubbles good.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper and heat until cheese is melted.
Put sliced potatoes in greased dish and pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 325° until potatoes are done.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: mexico chiquito punch
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients. Add enough water to make 1 gallon. Stir in 3 - 5 drops of food coloring.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells and let cool.
Beat milk in Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and sugar.
Whip well.
Put blueberries on top.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by spoonful.
Flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cookies freeze well.
Note no flour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Set aside.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into a measuring cup with a spout. Heat 1/2 cup vegetable shortening in a 10-inch frypan.
Test by dropping a small amount of batter into oil.
When it rises, oil is ready.
Drizzle batter into pan in a circular, thin stream.
As it turns golden and rises to surface, turn and cook other side.
Drain on towel.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
For each serving, place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on chicken.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks, if necessary.
Combine bread crumbs and seasoning. Dip each chicken roll in melted butter, then
in bread crumbs.
Arrange in shallow baking dish; drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake 40 minutes, or until chicken is tender.

title: piquant macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender; drain.
Rinse in cold water and drain in colander.
Mix vinegar, oil, paprika, salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Add macaroni and mix lightly; chill for 1 hour.
Cut meat, cheese, peppers, celery and scallions with macaroni mixture.
Toss lightly; chill thoroughly.
Garnish with pimento strips and watercress if desired.

title: barbecued beefies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Barbecue Sauce.
Shape mixture into 16 patties.
Place in ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Pour barbecue sauce over patties.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Combine ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Press into a hot dog keeper or container of equivalent size.
Let cool.
Unmold upside-down and break into pieces.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Clean hands.
Mix all together and roll in small ball.
Put in icebox.

title: barley soup - ham
directions: Boil barley 1 hour over medium-low heat in 3 to 4 cups of water.
Then add ham and bone and other remaining ingredients. Add more water as necessary to cover.
Continue to cook over medium-low heat until vegetables are cooked through.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Form into tiny balls.
Roll in cornstarch and fry in peanut oil.
(Or bake 20 minutes at 400°.)

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
In bowl, combine potatoes, cheese, onion, parsley and bread crumbs and mix well.
Turn into dish.
Blend salt, pepper, butter and milk.
Pour over potato mixture.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: big bucket in the sky chicken
directions: Mix all together; put in plastic bag.
Put pieces of chicken in and shake to coat chicken (one layer).
Melt butter in aluminum pan to cover bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with lemon and butter sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In large baking dish, lay pieces of chicken evenly.
Place one pat of butter on every piece of chicken (2 pats on the breasts).
Squeeze both lemons over chicken. Sprinkle lightly with the sweet basil, salt and pepper.
Turn down oven to 425°.
Bake for 1 hour until chicken is done.
Best when served with rice or noodles.

title: orange roughy with veggies
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add onion, zucchini, mushrooms and basil. Saute for 4 minutes.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper and place fillets over vegetables in skillet.
Arrange tomato slices over the fish.
Cover the skillet and simmer 8 or 9 minutes or until the fish flakes with a fork.
Uncover the skillet and sprinkle the cheese over the top.
Cover again and cook until the cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine nuts, dates, soda and salt.
Add shortening and water; allow 15 minutes to cool.
Stir to blend.
Beat eggs slightly; add vanilla.
Stir in sugar and flour.
Add to date mixture.
Don't overmix.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool before removing from pan.

title: easy broccoli souffle
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, soften butter.
Whisk in flour and then eggs.
Stir in cheeses, reserving some Cheddar for topping, about 1/2 cup.
Mix in broccoli.
Top with reserved cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: meltaway sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugars and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat smooth. Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill dough.
Form into walnut size balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13
x9-inch pan, melt butter. Sprinkle crumbs in and stir together; press into pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar together; set aside.
Mix milk and pudding mixes.
Fold in Cool Whip; mix softly.
Add creamed mixture to pudding mixture.
Alternate layers of pudding mixture with crushed cookies.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: eagle brand double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Top with chips and walnuts.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store at room temperature.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: twinkies cake
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise and lie down with cream filling face up in oblong 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Mix dry pudding and sour cream; spread over Twinkies.
Spread cherry pie filling next, then spread Cool Whip across top and sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate to chill before serving.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together and simmer 4 to 5 hours. Keeps well in refrigerator. Can be heated by the cup.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch date cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
(Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.)
Combine all ingredients except dates and nuts in large mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed until moistened, then beat at medium speed 1 minute.
By hand, stir in dates and nuts.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart, onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; remove from cookie sheets.
Make 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: wishing well cake
directions: Blend together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each until light and fluffy.
Stir in extract and salt.
Gradually blend flour in creamed mixture.
Turn onto greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes until cake tester comes clean.
Allow cake to cool a few minutes and turn out on plate.
Serve plain or with confectioners sugar sprinkled on.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients in the order listed.
Preheat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy iron skillet in 400° oven until very hot. Pour batter into skillet.
Turn oven to 375° and cook until golden brown.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Soak cabbage in cold salt water 1hour.
Boil in sufficient salt water to cover until almost tender.
Drain.
Remove center, leaving 4 layers of leaves, take center portion and shred.
Add hamburger, crumbs, onion, parsley, eggs, 2 tablespoons melted butter and seasonings.
Pack lightly in cabbage shell.
Mold and tie the leaves tightly to hold stuffing in place.
Place in casserole.
Baste with butter and 1 cup water combined.
Bake in slow oven (350°) about 35 to 45 minutes or 1 1/2 hours.
Cook hamburger very lightly to remove all fat, as long as you can mold into a ball.
Can refrigerate, slice, heat and serve as needed.

title: zesty spinach dip
directions: Drain roasted peppers thoroughly, chop roughly and set aside. Cook spinach according to pkg. Drain well then add roasted peppers. Stir in remaining ingredients
and chill mixture. For a decorative look place dip inside a cabbage head, bread bowl or large red pepper. Serve with crackers, bread chunks or assorted fresh vegetables.

title: 2 minute fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla until partially blended.
Put butter over top in center of dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth.
Blend in nuts.

title: quick and easy pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients
in a 9-inch pie plate.
Form into a nest. In a jar or with a whisk, mix oil and milk.
Pour into middle of flour mixture; mix well.
Press into pan.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes at 375°. Halfway through cooking, stir ingredients.

title: vegetable stroganoff
directions: In a skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Saute onion 2 to 3 minutes until soft.
Add mushrooms and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Spoon into slow cooker.
Add beans, carrots, tomato paste and wine or stock.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 4 hours, until most of the liquid has been absorbed.
In small saucepan, stir together cornstarch, yogurt and sour cream; heat gently over low heat for 1 minute (do not let sauce boil or it will curdle). Stir sauce into vegetable mixture.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add lump of butter; set aside. When cool, add the eggs.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. Add flour, sugar, oregano, garlic powder, tomato sauce and cottage cheese.
Pour spaghetti mixture into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with 6 slices of American cheese.
Pour hamburger mixture over cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Add the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted.
(Pepperoni is optional.)

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook onions until tender.
Combine hamburger, onion and all ingredients except noodles and sour cream.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, butter and eggs in large bowl; beat at low speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Stir in bananas and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients (flour, salt and soda).
Blend into creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes; cool.
Frost with Browned Butter Frosting.
Cut into bars for serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan, layer the rice and mushrooms, then the chicken pieces.
In a bowl, combine the condensed cream of onion soup, mushroom soup, water and dry onion soup mix.
Pour the mixture over the chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake in a 375° oven for 1 3/4 to 2 hours or until the rice is tender and the chicken is done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Stir flour, soda and salt. Cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter. Beat in vanilla and egg. Blend into flour mixture to make a smooth dough. Form into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Flatten dough balls by making crisscross fork patterns. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add potatoes. Cover with water, salt to taste and boil until potatoes are tender.
Add tuna, cook until hot.
Add milk and butter.
Cook until butter melts.
Serve with saltines or oyster crackers.
This recipe is quick and easy.

title: katy's punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.
During the holidays, you can float pecan halves.

title: italian fondue
directions: Brown beef in skillet and stir in tomato paste and cornstarch. Heat until warmed.
Put into fondue pot and place on low heat. Slowly stir in cheeses until they start to melt.
Add wine slowly and continue to stir until cheese is totally melted and ingredients are fully blended.
Add seasonings and stir well. Keep over low heat.
Using a fondue fork, dip the Italian chunk size bread into the mixture.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: mini party sandwiches
directions: Split rolls in half.
Spread Hormel chopped ham over bottom half.
Lay Swiss cheese slices over ham.
Put top back on rolls. Melt butter with poppy seed, onion flakes, dry mustard, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over rolls and bake until hot and cheese melts.

title: helen's brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together with melted chocolate and butter. Spread in 7 x 11-inch pan, lightly greased.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with favorite chocolate icing.
May be doubled for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vidalia onions and cucumbers
directions: Place cucumbers and onion in a bowl.
Sprinkle with the salt and set aside.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and pepper in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over the vegetables. Let cool, then cover and refrigerate.
Serve after the second or third day for maximum flavor.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix well and spread over top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in oil and butter.
Mix with other ingredients.
Press into ungreased angel food cake pan (2-piece). Let stand overnight.
Slice with sharp knife.

title: christina's stuffed peppers
directions: Wash and core peppers; set aside.

Chop onion and saute in oil until translucent. Add the ground beef and cook until pink is gone and beef is crumbly. Add the rice and continue to saute for 6 to 8 minutes. Season with seasoned salt and pepper.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and set aside.
Cook broccoli with onion; drain well.
Add cheese, soup, rice and milk to broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 300° until hot.

title: spiced percolator punch
directions: In a 30 cup percolator bottom put first 4 ingredients.
In the basket put remaining ingredients.
Plug the percolator in and when the light comes on it is ready.
Serve hot.

title: jello slices
directions: Mix Jell-O and Knox mix together as by package.
Chill slightly until soft gel.
Add applesauce and stir until mixed together.
Add fruit of choice; pour into a baking pan or cake pan.
Chill until hard.
Serve on head of lettuce, sliced.

title: pineapple cowboy cake
directions: In a bowl mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Put marshmallows in a pan and cook for 5 minutes.
Put in the Rice Krispies.
Stir it up.
Eat them with your hands.
They taste good.

title: easy cheese batter bread
directions: Melt butter in warm milk and water.
In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and all other ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining 1 cup flour.
Cover. Let rise in warm place until light, 45 to 60 minutes.
(Dough does not double in size.)
Generously grease bottom and sides of 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Stir down dough.
Place in greased pan.
Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Cube bread. Add all other ingredients. Put in a bowl with lid. Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, take out and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour until brown and cooked, no lid. Do not stir while baking.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar, flour, soda, vanilla and a few apples together. Add apples, dates and pecans. Should be real stiff; if not, add a little more flour and sugar. Bake in Bundt pan on 250° to 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and cocoa in mixing bowl.
In a saucepan, bring to boil 1 cup of water, cooking oil and stick of margarine.
Pour into bowl with dry ingredients and add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into broiler pan or a jelly roll pan with sides.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Bring spaghetti to a boil and cook until tender.
Drain and run under cold water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate. (Great side dish for cookouts.)

title: microwave baked beans
directions: Place bacon and onion in microwave-safe dish.
Cook, covered, on High for about 2 1/2 minutes.
Add beans and other ingredients; mix well.
Cook, covered, 5 minutes on High; reduce heat and cook additional 10 to 12 minutes on Medium.
