Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain off drippings.
Stir in 1/2 package taco seasoning.
Set aside.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells and bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crunch pea salad
directions: Mix peas, celery, cashews and onions.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing.
Pour over first ingredients and chill.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix lemon jello with boiling water to dissolve.
Cool.
Mix cake mix, oil, eggs (added one at a time) and lemon extract.
Pour into cake pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Punch holes in cake while still hot.
Spread icing.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup of margarine, and put into a greased baking dish.
Top with corn flakes and 1/4 cup of margarine.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
With mixer, blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add rhubarb and dry ingredients. Stir until thoroughly combined.
Pour into one unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 25 minutes.
Cover pie with topping and place under broiler until lightly browned.
Watch carefully to avoid burning.

title: sweet and sour meatball appetizers
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Set aside.
Combine chili, jelly and lemon juice in saucepan or deep frying pan and mix well over low heat.
Add meatballs, stirring lightly.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Can be warmed in a crock-pot.

title: mrs. eisenhower's million dollar fudge
directions: Mix sugar, salt, butter or margarine and evaporated milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 14 to 15 minutes or to 235°, stirring constantly.

title: christmas turkey
directions: Cook turkey at 400° for 3 hours or until turkey is tender, basting with oleo.
Wrap turkey in foil.

title: cheesy chicken tortilla stack
directions: Heat oil to 375° in skillet.
Fry tortilla, one at a time, for 3 to 5 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Combine sour cream, salt and hot sauce.

title: zucchini salad
directions: In a medium bowl stir relish, vinegar, sugar and salt; add zucchini.
Toss gently.
Cover and refrigerate about 30 minutes, tossing occasionally.
Line bowl with lettuce.
Spoon zucchini mixture into bowl.

title: never fail egg whites
directions: Beat egg whites until they begin to stiffen.
Add powdered sugar and clear vanilla.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Put on pies.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces and shape into balls.
In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll each ball in cinnamon sugar mix.
Arrange evenly in a greased 10 inch floured tube pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon sugar mix.
Combine butter and brown sugar and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 minutes before placing bread on serving plate.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocado and remove seed.
Mash pulp completely.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Add chili powder, garlic and Miracle Whip. Season.
Serve with king size corn chips.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position in oven and preheat to 425°. Spoon apple filling into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk, eggs, flavoring and nutmeg.
Pour over apples.
Combine sugar and flour; cut in remaining 1/4 cup margarine until crumbly.
Stir in granola. Sprinkle over pie.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Place ground meat in covered casserole in microwave.
Cook about 4 minutes and drain fat.
Transfer to skillet and brown meat with onion.
Add chili powder, catsup and salt.
Mash kidney beans and add to the skillet.
Place in a casserole and top with the cheese, olives and green onions.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: special potato salad
directions: Remove skins from potatoes.
Chop eggs with potato masher. Combine all together and mix well (the secret is to combine while potatoes and eggs are warm and onions and celery are at room temperature).
After cooling, place in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to the pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes before removing to a wire rack.
Cool completely.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut venison into 3/4-inch strips. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over meat and refrigerate, covered, overnight. Drain; hang meat over the racks in oven and bake at 150° to 170° for 6 hours, until meat is dried.

title: savory chicken-stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, but do not let stand as directed on package.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix well.
Cover tightly and let stand 24 hours.
Shake crackers a couple times in the 24 hour period.

title: sunshine fudge
directions: Combine marmalade, cream, and corn syrup in blender or food processor.
Process until well blended.
In a large saucepan, combine the sugar and cocoa.
Mix well. Add softened butter along with milk/marmalade mixture.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture reaches the soft ball stage.
This should take about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla extract. Place pan in large pan of cold water and allow to cool before beating.
Beat until mixture thickens and is no longer glossy. This could take up to 20 or 30 minutes.
Drop from a spoon onto wax paper or pour into well-buttered 8 inch square dish or pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange apples in greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Bake and cool.
While cake cools, mix jello by directions on box; set aside.
Take cooled cake and punch holes in top of cake.
Pour jello mixture over top of cake, then frost with Cool Whip.
Slice strawberries on top. Chill in refrigerator.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Put carrots in casserole, alternating with cheese.
Pour onions and butter over top, then sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: microwave minestrone
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable bowl, combine carrots, celery, zucchini, yellow pepper and onion. Drizzle with oil and toss to coat. Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on High for 15 minutes. Serves 5.

title: one pot pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, brown chops; pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
(This can be altered to as few or as many pork chops as you want.
The more pork chops you use, the more of the other ingredients you use.)

title: chocolate rolls
directions: Mix cake as directed on package. Pour into 2 heavily greased and floured 12 x 18-inch pans. Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 8 minutes. Turn out onto lightly floured towels; cover cakes with pans until cool. Cut each cake in half to make 4 strips about 5 x 16-inches. Trim off crisp edges. Roll cakes with towels into 16-inch long rolls. When cakes are cool, soften gelatin in 3/4 cup water and bring to boil, stirring constantly. Add frosting mix. Beat in warm bowl until fluffy. Unroll cakes and spread with frosting. Let set for 20 minutes. Re-roll cakes, wrap loosely in towels and chill for at least 2 hours. Cut rolls into 3/4-inch slices with a sharp, wet knife. Makes about 88 slices.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with dipping size pieces of King's Hawaiian bread.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine. Add cocoa and stir. Add sugar, flour, eggs and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: mustard potatoes
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until almost done.
Place in large, greased baking dish.
Chop onion fine.
Melt butter in skillet; add onion and cook until it is limp.
Stir in flour smoothly and gradually add stock or bouillon.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until it bubbles.
Season with salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook very slowly, about 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill until served.

title: chocolate-berry frozen dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil.
In
a large bowl, beat 2 (6 ounce) packages cream cheese.
Blend in syrup and water. Beat until smooth. Fold in 3 cups whipped topping.
Spoon half of the chocolate mixture into prepared pan. Freeze 15 minutes. Chill remaining mixture.

In small bowl, beat remaining cream cheese. Beat in strawberries until smooth. Fold in remaining 1 1/2 cups topping. Spoon strawberry mixture over chocolate layer in pan. Top with chilled chocolate mix.
Cover and freeze several hours or overnight.
Unmold 10 minutes before serving. Peel off foil. Makes 10 servings.

title: quick spareribs
directions: First, cut ribs into serving pieces.
Wash and place in two quarts of water.
Cover and boil until good and tender in a large pot.
Drain and place ribs in baking pan or dish.
Baste your ribs liberally with bottled barbecue sauce or sauce of your choice.

title: dream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Cut layers in half to make 4 layers.

title: venison roast
directions: Flour roast and brown on both sides in bacon fat.
Place in baking pan and cover with water.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven until roast is tender.
Remove from oven, add vegetables and seasonings and return to oven.
Cover and cook until vegetables are done.
Gravy can be made by browning flour and using the broth, if desired.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Chill. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers, potato chips, pretzels or vegetables.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet with butter.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch cubes and spread in a baking dish.
Cover with half the meat.
Add half the soup and a sliced onion.
Season with salt and pepper. Repeat, using remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. More soup may be added during baking, if needed.

title: quick and easy chicken divine
directions: Broil or bake seasoned chicken for 30 minutes.
Then drain off fat.
Combine the soups with water.
Stir until lumps are gone. Add chopped mushrooms and almonds. Then add salt, pepper, garlic salt, onion salt and red pepper.
Stir mixture and then pour over chicken.
Simmer for 15 minutes on low.
Serve with rice.

title: apple strips
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in 3/4 cup margarine; add milk.
Roll out half of dough in a jelly roll pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and parsley.
Roll into ball. Roll ball in nuts and parsley.
Chill and serve.

title: gabriele's wiener schnitzel for four(serves 4)
directions: Flatten pork cutlets with meat hammer until cutlets are 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle the cutlets with salt and pepper.
Coat each cutlet with flour.
Take 1 egg and 1 tablespoon of milk and beat with a fork.
Dip the cutlets in the egg mixture, then coat them with bread crumbs.
Fry on both sides quickly (golden brown) in butter or margarine.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Can be topped with Rice Krispies or seasoned crumbs mixed with butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, brown sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: special mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil for 30 minutes or until tender. Drain.
Set aside.
Place corn meal and milk in skillet, then add potatoes.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with 1 cup onions until brown.
Add can of enchilada sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer until hot. In very large casserole dish, place tortilla chips to cover bottom.
Add hamburger mixture to cover chips, layer two cheeses, olives and onions.
Start layering again with chips, mixture, etc. Top layer to be chips and cheese.
Heat in oven (or microwave) until cheese is melted and all is hot.
If you think it may be dry, add an extra can of enchilada sauce over the top of casserole and heat.
You can also add diced green chilies to the meat mixture, or layer them.
For large family, or leftovers are great. You can even adjust down for your family.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese with the 1/2 cup sugar.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water, then cool.
Whip Milnot.
Mix cheese/sugar mixture and jello.
Add Milnot.
Pour into pans lined with graham crackers.
Top with a few graham cracker crumbs.
Mixture will look thin until refrigerated and has set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Prepare cookie dough the day before you plan on rolling and cutting.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until just golden.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery in microwave, then mix all ingredients together and turn into a buttered dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grammy's meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Drain excess broth if necessary.

title: spiced grape jelly
directions: Sterilize 10 (8 ounce) jelly glasses.
Leave in hot water until ready to fill.
In a large kettle, combine sugar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice with 3 cups water; mix well.
Cook, stirring, over high heat to dissolve sugar.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly; boil hard for 1 minute, stirring.

title: easy pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over pork chops.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes!

title: spiced peaches
directions: Combine all except peaches.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches and chill.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Put in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Save out 1/2 cup.
Melt 3/4 bag of little marshmallows or 35 big ones into milk.
Mix with cream, whipped.
Pour half of mixture over crumbs.
Add cherry pie mix and spread evenly.
Add remaining cream mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Refrigerate. Enjoy.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine jello with crushed pineapple.
Bring to a boil.
Add 2 cups buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Put in a larger low Tupperware dish and congeal.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Peel and cut into bite-size pieces.
(You may want to leave skin on.)
Chop onions and celery. Add to potatoes along with mayonnaise and dill relish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add sprinkle of Creole seasoning to taste.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Mix and pour over chicken.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This is a good diet dish.
If you are not dieting, take the liquid after cooking, thicken with flour to make gravy and serve over rice.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, salt, vanilla and chocolate syrup. Mix in flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Do not overbake.
They may not look done. Cool.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Drain canned vegetables.
Layer in casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour over layered vegetables.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Break eggs into blender container.
Add onion, salt and 1/2 of potatoes.
Blend on low speed for a few seconds.
Remove cover insert with blender on.
Add flour and remaining potatoes.
Mix parsley into mixture.
Pour into hot greased frying pan.
(You might want to add more potatoes.)

title: eva's salami
directions: Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Once a day for 3 days, mix well.
Keep hands wet to keep from sticking.
On the 4th day, mix and divide meat into 5 rolls about the size of a half dollar.
Lay on broiler pan.
Bake 5 hours at 175°.

title: mrs. joe's applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add raisins, applesauce and fruit juice.
Add flour, a small amount at a time; mix well.
Add hot water and soda mix into ingredients.
Add spices, chopped dates and cherries. Cook at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or lower temperature according to your stove's heat capacity.

title: chocolate coconutty bread pudding
directions: Place the bread crumbs in a buttered, square cake pan.
Beat eggs thoroughly; add to bread crumbs.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well with a spoon.

title: oven buttered corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt butter in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Mix biscuit mix and corn together, making soft dough.
Knead about 15 strokes.
Roll out on floured surface and cut strips about 3-inches long and 1-inch wide.
Dip in melted butter, arrange in single layer in pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: calico coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine coleslaw blend, corn, olives and onions; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; blend well.
Add to coleslaw mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: peach pickles(salty)
directions: Boil
the
water
and Hawaiian salt; cool and pour over peaches.
Soak overnight.
Drain.
Boil the sugar and vinegar; pour when cool.
Red coloring may be added.

title: peas oregano
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients and stir to mix.
Add peas.
Cook on low heat covered about 8 to 10 minutes or until cooked and tender.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture has the appearance of coarse cornmeal.
Lightly, add water.
Roll on a floured board. Makes 2 crusts.

title: "karie's" oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Melt Crisco before adding it and sift flour, soda and spices.
Drop by teaspoon on greased pan or baking sheet.
Cook in moderate oven at 350°.

title: creole zucchini
directions: Cook onion, garlic and green pepper in hot oil in skillet until soft.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Serve topped with parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: roast wild goose
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash goose in cold water.
Drain well and pat dry inside and out.
Remove fat gland and base of tail. Sprinkle cavity with salt and pepper.
Stuff with equal amounts of	celery,
green	onions (tops included) and apple. Rub
skin with bacon grease.	Place goose on rack breast side up
or	on V-shaped rack with breast side down, if preferred. Roast
at 500° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and roast
for	3 hours,
basting
frequently.
If breast side is down,
turn breast
side
up when three-fourths done.
Remove goose
from oven.
Let	stand
15 minutes before carving.
In small
saucepan, make
gravy.
Thicken
chicken bouillon with flour,
stirring
to paste
with cold water.
Skim excess fat from
pan
drippings. Add
tablespoons fat free drippings. Cook
over	low
heat until
blended.
Add
currant jelly and sherry.
Reheat
but
do not boil.
Serve with sauerkraut and gin.

title: california strawberry log
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Generously grease and oil.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook on simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: golden pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: jello pie
directions: Put ingredients into a pan together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly as it heats.
Then set aside to cool.
Line pie plates with vanilla wafers.
Whip 1 can of milk; add to first mixture and whip again.
Put in lined pie pans and put in refrigerator to set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: delicious ham loaf
directions: Mix meats together well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into a roll and wrap in heavy foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Top with the topping.

title: appetizer chicken puffs
directions: Stir Parmesan cheese into Cream Puff Pastry.
Spoon mixture into decorating bag fitted with a No. 5 or 6B large, fluted tip. Pipe mixture into 30 small balls on lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool away from drafts.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat and make into a simple syrup the sugar and water. Mix ingredients and add to the cooled syrup mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Put pudding mixture into molds and freeze.

title: 6 egg cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and add the sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each egg.
Add flour, then add vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in batter and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes 325°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Let cookie dough get soft.
Put some water on hands before spreading onto pizza pan.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8-10 minutes. Let cool completely.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread over dough.
Arrange fruit over dough in layers. Mix orange juice, sugar and cornstarch together.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Let it cool a little and pour over fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: eye wash
directions: Boil and cool; wash eyes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine, oil, chocolate and water in saucepan and heat until chocolate is melted.
Combine flour, soda, sugar, milk, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla in a large bowl, then combine with first mixture.
Pour batter in greased 12 x 18-inch cake pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy m&m cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and both sugars.
Stir in vanilla. Mix together flour, salt and soda; add to shortening.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: party rolls
directions: Split rolls in half.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Spread on both sides of rolls.
Lay cheese slices and then put ham slices on rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
You can freeze these before cooking and use later.

title: lake country dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Toss with oil and vinegar.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: pound cake (sour cream)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and flavoring.
Fold in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Spread coconut on bottom of well greased 15 X11 X12-inch baking pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello 1 in cup hot water.
Add pineapple juice with water to make 1 cup.
When jello begins to congeal, add pineapple, cottage cheese and marshmallows.
Stir thoroughly; pour into shallow dish.
When completely congealed, mix mayonnaise with cream cheese and spread on top.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, flour and reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart dish. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Pour batter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients and let stand 1 hour.

title: ne plus ultra pesto(for pesto, the simpler, the better)
directions: I usually leave out the cheese and mix it in just prior to serving, as it is less messy.

title: marinated chicken kabobs
directions: Stir dressing mix, juice and oil in large bowl.
Add chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Heat broiler.
Arrange chicken and vegetables on skewers.
Broil 3 inches from heat 16 minutes or until cooked through, turning frequently.
Discard any remaining marinade.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Place vegetables and meat in Dutch oven.
Add seasonings. Pour tomato soup over all and add 2 cans of water.
Stir.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 5 hours, covered.
Serve with biscuits or French bread.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Melt butter in chafing dish or skillet. Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until tender. Stir in sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings. Add shrimp. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until heated through. (Sauce is traditionally thin so it can be absorbed by rice at serving time.)

title: microwave easy caramel rolls
directions: Combine sugar, butter and water in 1-quart glass casserole. Microwave for about 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir in nuts.
Separate biscuits; cut each one into quarters.
Add biscuits to sugar mixture.
Stir to coat each one.
Push biscuits and coating away from center of casserole and set a custard cup, open end up, in center.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, onion, cheeses, soup, salt and pepper.
Place in casserole.
Mix crushed cornflakes and butter together and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Reserve enough whipped cream for a small amount on top of each serving.
Combine remaining ingredients and sweeten with powdered sugar.
Mix well and chill.
Spoon into parfait glasses; top each with whipped cream and a fresh strawberry.

title: shepherd's pie(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Prepare potatoes.
Beat egg; set aside.
In skillet, brown meat and onion; blend in next 5 ingredients.
Add milk and undrained peas and carrots.
Cook until slightly thickened.
In 1-quart greased casserole, place 1/2 potatoes; top with meat and remaining potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave lemon butter sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-cup glass measure. Cook, uncovered, on High (max power) 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until hot and butter is melted. Stir. Serve immediately with seafood, hot green vegetables.

title: french fried toast
directions: Hand-mix first 7 ingredients (all but bread and oil).
Dip 1/2 slice of bread into batter.
Drop in hot oil until browned.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Cut remaining tortillas in half.
Layer chicken mixture, cut tortillas and cheese and repeat. Cover and bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Remove foil last 10 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in 1 block of butter until soft. Add the soups and pimento.
Mix and heat until melted. Add the seafood and Tabasco sauce. Cook about 15 to 20 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and put in casserole dish. Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water the chocolate chips and butter.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts to coat well.
Make well in center of flour mixture.
In small bowl, combine chocolate mixture, sour cream, corn syrup and egg until blended.
Add to dry ingredients; stir until just moistened. Spoon into paper lined muffin pans, filling each about 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely, or serve warm.
Makes about 15 muffins.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix together, sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon. Melt margarine; add sugar mixture and beaten egg.
Stir in vanilla and raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; top with crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° until done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and lemon juice and put in a buttered Pyrex dish.
Mix rest of ingredients until crumbly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cake
directions: Add eggs and oleo to dry ingredients; mix well.
Add peaches. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a sheet cake pan which has been greased and floured.

title: the ultimate chocolate frosting
directions: In small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine to soften.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk.
Beat until of spreading consistency, adding 1 tablespoon milk, if needed.
Add vanilla.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: lime and pineapple chiffon
directions: Combine lime gelatin and pineapple in bowl; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
May be served immediately or chilled until serving time.

title: corn dinner cole slaw
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well and add to the cabbage.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream
margarine
and sugar together until smooth.
Add the egg
yolk
and
mix in thoroughly.	Sift the flour and add the cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to the creamed mixture, using your hands
to blend thoroughly. Spread evenly over the entire surface of	a greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Beat the egg white slightly
and
spread
on
top
of	batter.
Press	nuts overall. Bake in
275° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in 1 1/2 squares when still hot.

title: mom's ginger cream cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Add to shortening mixture along with 1/2 cup molasses. Sift together flour and spices and add to mixture.
Chill dough. Drop by spoonful 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Glaze with 10x sugar and milk, if desired.

title: abe's apple cake
directions: Sift sugar, soda, flour, spices and salt together into a bowl. Add eggs, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add apples and nuts and stir until mixed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cake from oven.
Place in heavy brown paper bag immediately.
Close tightly and let stand until cool.
Serve with Caramel Sauce.

title: mom's hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and lukewarm water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add warm water, sugar, salt, melted butter and flour. Put on a floured board and knead well.
Let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
Shape in rolls and let rise until double again.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Put in well-greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add sugar, butter and salt to warm sweet potatoes. Beat well. Add cream, beaten eggs, vanilla and lemon.
Pour into unbaked 8 or 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light; add and beat well remaining ingredients.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan; do not invert.
Yields 20 pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Sift flour into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add with rest of ingredients to the flour in large bowl.
Mix well until all ingredients are blended.
Pour into greased pans and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap in freezer paper to freeze.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Add the ingredients that have been soaking for 3 hours.
Let simmer until rinds turn brown.
Do not let boil.
Seal in jars.

title: cheese ball with beef
directions: For best results, place dried beef in freezer until nearly frozen.
Tear into several pieces and blend in the blender.
Use half of the pecans, parsley flakes and beef in the cheese ball and the other half as a coating.
For best results in forming the ball, refrigerate several hours.
Form a ball in Saran Wrap and then coat with the items listed.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: In 3-quart saucepan combine potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain, mash potatoes gradually stirring in salad dressing, cream cheese, onion powder, salt and pepper until light and fluffy.
Spoon in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until thoroughly heated.

title: french tea cakes(petite gateaux douce)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and cream until smooth, adding vanilla.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well until you have a soft, smooth dough.
Roll out on a floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
(Last several weeks.)
These were usually stored in a cloth sack or pillowcase and brought on the boats by fishermen to have with their coffee.

title: chinese crispies
directions: Melt spry and put in chips.
Stir until melted.
Add nuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: cinnamon pecan squares
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add the flour, egg yolk,
vanilla
and
cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients well, then press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press the pecans into the mixture.
Beat
the
egg white until foamy, then spread on top. Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares immediately.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients well.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese (parsley and paprika are optional).
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be made a day ahead and frozen, baked or uncooked. Serves 12.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as follows:
cauliflower, broccoli, eggs, olives and water chestnuts.
In another bowl, mix mayo, sugar and lemon juice to taste to cover vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add other ingredients as given.
Let stand few minutes or I prefer to chill before rolling on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter; bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread roll
directions: Roll out softened dough to 10 x 15 inches.
Spread with melted butter.
Lay pepperoni all over.
Spread with grated cheese.
Roll up and butter top.
Make slits along top before baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: supper on bread
directions: Mix all together and pack into French bread after you cut the top center out.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until meat is done.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° until done, approximately 25 minutes. Top with 2 tablespoons reserved cheese.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Heat butter in skillet. Add ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes. Add cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serves 4 or more.

title: mountain mama mud slide
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamy.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix both puddings with 2 cups milk.
Spread on cream cheese layer, then top with rest of Cool Whip.
Grate chocolate bar on top.

title: potato tot casserole
directions: Pat meat firmly in baking dish. Pour soup over evenly. Put chopped onion and Tater Tots on top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: garlic chive potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes in a large pot with enough water to cover. Boil for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done; drain and set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: You also need one 7-inch flowerpot and plastic flowers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate until use.
Serve with chunks of bread.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean the broccoli and cut into florets. Mix together with the cheese, bacon and onion. Mix together the sugar, vinegar and mayo. Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: special layered salad
directions: In a 3-quart bowl or dish, layer the romaine, green pepper, onion, peas, mayonnaise and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight. Just before serving, top with shrimp, bacon, tomato and eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until smooth.
Use as a dip for any fruit.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, light corn syrup, vanilla and salt and blend well.
Gradually stir in sifted sugar until creamy consistency is reached.
You may not need quite all of the sugar.
Knead until smooth.
Add chopped nuts.
Pack into buttered 8-inch square pan.
When firm, cut in squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain French beans, peas and corn.
Set aside vegetables. Make marinade with sugar, black pepper, salt, vegetable oil and white vinegar.
Bring to a boil in a saucepan.
Let cool.
Add vegetables and let set overnight.
Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces on top then sprinkle with the dried onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 1/4 hours (remove cover and let brown the last 10 minutes).

title: mini calzones
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Cut each biscuit horizontally, making 20 thin biscuits. Gently press each biscuit into an oval shape and place a slice of pepperoni or a little piece of spinach with a level teaspoon of cheese filling. Moisten edges of dough and fold over to enclose filling. Pinch edges carefully to seal. Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then serve with warm marinara sauce.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in kettle, stirring to break up meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until yellow.
Add remaining vegetables and cook, stirring often, 3 minutes. Stir in flour. Add 6 cups boiling water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together; stir in sugar.
Add eggs and salt and beat together.
Stir in flour and vanilla just until mixed.
Pour into oiled pie pan and bake 20 minutes at 350.

title: quick fish-potato supper
directions: Break up potatoes; set aside.
In a bowl, combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in potatoes and cheese.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange fish sticks atop.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until center is nearly set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Add vegetables, meat and seasonings to eggs.
Pour into a well oiled skillet in a thin layer.
Cook over medium heat until brown on bottom.
Remove to broiler and brown top.
Transfer to hot serving dish and pour sauce over the top.

title: mexican chocolate cooler
directions: Combine 1/2 cup water, sugar and cinnamon.
Boil 1 minute. Add remaining 3/4 cup water.
Pour into 12 muffin tin cups and freeze.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend ingredients and serve cold or serve hot.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese and bread crumbs or crushed potato chops.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine chopped apples with sugar and set aside.
To the slightly beaten eggs, add the salad oil and vanilla and beat well. Add the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and mix.
Combine flour mixture and apple mixture by hand and add chopped nuts.
Cool and frost.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Season chicken breasts lightly with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in skillet and brown chicken about 5 minutes on each side, pressing flat with spatula.
While chicken browns, combine sour cream, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Spoon over chicken and warm through a minute or two.
Sprinkle with chopped chives, if desired, and serve.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, soda and salt.
Beat the 1 cup margarine 30 seconds.
Add brown sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla; beat well.
Stir in all dry ingredients.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch chips with vegetable oil in a double boiler until chips are melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add nuts and chow mein noodles.
Stir to coat all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let stand until set, about 15 minutes.
Store leftovers in airtight container.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix flour, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in oblong pan.
When cooked, spoon on 1 jar marshmallow cream while cake is hot.
After cake is cool, add frosting.

title: sack sausage
directions: You will also need muslin bags big enough for 2 soft drink cans to fit into and string to tie bags.

title: beth's vegetable and philly sauce
directions: Butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: egg-olive sandwich filling
directions: Peel eggs and chop.
Add mayonnaise and chopped olives.
Pour enough olive juice into mixture to make mixture spreadable as a sandwich filling.
Refrigerate.
Yields 2 to 3 sandwiches.

title: easy chocolate dessert(the magic of the microwave)
directions: Microwave (High) chocolate pieces in uncovered 1-quart glass Mix 'N' Pour bowl for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until glossy.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in beaten eggs.
Microwave (High), uncovered, 30 to 45
seconds or until slightly thickened.
Cool 10 minutes. Fold in whipped topping and cake cubes.
Transfer to serving dish. Refrigerate until set, 2 to 3 hours.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: *Cook pudding with 1 1/2 cups juice from oranges, pineapple and cherries.
